(for Login)',0,0,0,10000,1,'2019-11-05 12:45:56','2019-11-05 18:15:56'),(56,'5dc2afc3b3c34',8,467,'Unfair harassment case handling in corporate offices ','15000','Screenshot_20191106_170156_com.android.chrome.jpg','https://callupon.org/st4','Women who raise voice against harassment at work place have been more victimised at scrutinised and caused further ill treatment. File petition for their job security and fair laws on these. Managers in India get away inspite of these rules because of retaliation on the complaints. ',0,0,0,25000,1,'2019-11-06 11:34:27','2019-11-06 17:04:27'),(57,'5dc52c1875763',3,1,'Health is health','Health','IMG_20191106_173646_879.jpg','https://callupon.org/st5','<span style=\"font-size:10px;\">B IU</span>',0,0,0,23,1,'2019-11-08 08:49:28','2019-11-08 14:19:28'),(58,'5de353213cbae',5,21,'love','love','img6.jpg','https://callupon.org/st6','how are u<br />\r\n how are u<br />\r\nhow are u   how are u how are u how are uhow are u',0,0,0,112,1,'2019-12-01 05:44:01','2019-12-01 11:14:01'),(59,'5de3907415f18',8,21,'A Doctor who Saves Others Life was Herself Helpless','A Doctor who Saves Others Life was Herself Helpless','nirbhaya-rape-case_1531152272.jpg','https://callupon.org/st7','<strong>A Doctor who Saves Others Life was Herself Helpless</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>Priyanka Reddy, a Veterinary Doctor faced a brutal sexual assault, murdered and burnt alive. Today the entire social media is asking for her justice: Justice required for Priyanka Reddy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People are so enthusiast with great aggression asking for justice wherein, everyone demanded that punishment like hanging to death is not enough.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Obviously, “sentenced to death” is not a sufficient pay-off for these brutal actions. But, what about the daily happenings in the society where there are a lot of rape cases and only a few get highlighted.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Woman – an idol or an element of SEX</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>In today’s 21st century, where a woman has all the equivalent rights as that of man, can perform all such stuff which a common man does & is still unsafe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why threatening scenarios still exist in the nation where on Navratri an idol of a woman is worshipped and is raped in common days. Just because of a female’s natural body assets, how come a society can decide and address her standard of living and sense of dressing. Why not males can change their mindset?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Equivalent Rights in a Male Dominant Society</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, women have indeed got all those rights which a man holds but still, unfortunately, women survive in a male dominating society. India, a country rich in technology and agriculture still lacks much behind when it comes to justice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Several cases came into existence which got viral for a week and a month and got closed unexpectedly with no petition and solution. We have heard several cases such as Asifa Rape Case, well renowned 2012 Delhi Gang Rape, Aarushi Talwar’s Murder Case and a lot more. If anyone could have got a proper justice then, no other case would have appeared, unlike today. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Presently, the situation has become so drastic and worst that even minor children have become a victim of rape. Most of the time, people talk about morals and values but what is happening today comprises no hide and seeks. Whenever any such incident happens, people act and behave too aggressively and sooner with time everyone forgets and moves on. No one withstands and fights for their rights and so does the judgmental bodies. Showcasing different victims in a single case alas!!! unfortunately, the case becomes a mystery with no clarification about the accused and the victim.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>It\'s not about anyone, it\'s about us</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>We need to be strong enough in all the states specifically mentally, physically and emotionally. Luckily because nothing has happened to us doesn’t mean that we can’t support anyone. Any country is with its citizens or a country and a nation exists because of its residents. Thus, take a stand and be strong enough. This is because, if citizens are aware of their rights and can fight for the same then, no enemy or a rapist can threaten you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A female who had become a victim is someone’s daughter, sister, wife, and friend and to all the males, the unforgettable activities that you do with someone’s girl could happen to your girls as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is what Karma says: what goes, comes around.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>So, a small message to all…</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Be strong, Be Aware… File a Petition and Fly Like a Flair.</p>\r\n',0,0,0,20000,2,'2019-12-01 10:05:40','2019-12-10 10:38:19'),(60,'5de65306a754f',2,497,'Acid Attack','Public Awareness','Acid-Attack-From-Pain-To-Purpose.jpg','https://callupon.org/st8','Acid Attack - a Forceful Acceptance or Unwanted Rejection by the Society<br />\r\nVictims of Acid Attack are actually not the victims but the survivors in the society. But,<br />\r\nunfortunately, the people who do so on the bodies and faces of pretty and beautiful<br />\r\nladies require to cover their faces.<br />\r\nWhat would happen to snatch away the beauty of a beauty?<br />\r\nHere, the beauty of beauty means the beautiful physical appearance of a female which<br />\r\nsome societal monsters take away.<br />\r\nIndia has seen many cases and faces of acid attacks where the victims reveal both their<br />\r\ninner beauty and strength to accept the harsh reality of their reshaped physical<br />\r\nappearance. Alongside government, you need to take action withstanding strong at this<br />\r\nsocietal threat.<br />\r\nCases over Cases Revealing Victims<br />\r\nMake culture and society so strong that a woman can fearlessly cross a man outside<br />\r\nher home. There have been many victims such as<br />\r\nReshma Qureshi, who was just 17 years old, lost her vision. The saddest, harsh and<br />\r\nunacceptable reality is that her relatives and their friends collectively were involved in<br />\r\nthrowing acid on her face.<br />\r\nLakshmi Aggarwal, who was again a 17 years old girl, became a victim of a brutal acid<br />\r\nattack by her acquaintances.<br />\r\nDifferent Victims, Different Sufferings<br />\r\nWhereas, both the victims have their sufferings and pains but both of them have<br />\r\ninspired the society with their belief and strength. The mental trauma of losing your<br />\r\nnatural physical appearance haunts the most simultaneously the taunts of the society<br />\r\nand people passing by.<br />\r\nYes, not everyone rejects the victim of an acid attack but not everyone accepts them.<br />\r\nDeep inside the heart people always keep guilt and fear of untouchably and don’t<br />\r\naccept them.<br />\r\nUnanswerable Whys…<br />\r\nBut, the alarming question here is, why to throw acid on a face? Why haunt a person to<br />\r\nsuch an extent that without being in any malpractice they have to hide their face and<br />\r\nhave to ask for dignity? Why to forcefully feel pity for such victims where there are no<br />\r\n<br />\r\nflaws? There is ‘n’ number of Why(s) that both the society and governmental bodies<br />\r\nneed to answer.<br />\r\nSympathy or Empathy? Does inner beauty really matter or is just a matter of<br />\r\nwords?<br />\r\nMost of the time, people say that inner beauty, good heart, and hard work means<br />\r\neverything but deep inside, everyone goes beyond physical beauty and appearance.<br />\r\nThis is just to show the sympathy or a kind of show-off towards the victims of acid<br />\r\nattack.<br />\r\nThe bitter, as well as the harshest reality, is that society is cruel because when people<br />\r\ntaunt everyone on body shaming focusing on height, weight, health, complexion and<br />\r\nphysique then, acid attack is a big deal to tackle with.<br />\r\nSuch victims are not the culprits to be treated helpless in fact, why to make them a<br />\r\nvictim? When a person who gets targeted for an acid attack without even knowing, is<br />\r\nalso a human being. They haven’t lost the natural beauty of their own or accidentally.<br />\r\nThey face a loss of their face or body because of brutal planning by some societal<br />\r\nmonsters.<br />\r\nDignity is ALL Above<br />\r\nSuch people have equal rights to live in society as they used to live abreast with<br />\r\ncomplete dignity and respect. Also, instead of hiding your face and feeling ashamed,<br />\r\nyou should step ahead towards the culprits more strongly with gratitude that you are a<br />\r\nbeautiful creation of God and nothing can stop you doing all such stuff that you are fond<br />\r\nof.<br />\r\nDo not feel sorry instead live more of yourself without the guilt of not having beautiful<br />\r\nskin or face. Beauty is from the heart and inner beauty reflects from one&#39;s face and<br />\r\nthoughts because the face is the mirror of the heart.',0,0,0,2000,3,'2019-12-03 12:20:22','2019-12-04 15:28:54'),(61,'5de65495dc252',7,498,'LPG','Environmental Issue','figXdPUQoCtMaVv-800x450-noPad.jpg','https://callupon.org/st9','LPG Replaced Chulhas Still BPL People are Out of its Reach<br />\r\nUjjwala Scheme introduced by the government has benefitted people to an extent<br />\r\nthat simultaneously, it has also left people in the drastic effects. According to the<br />\r\ngovernment’s data, Ujjwala Scheme targeted 5 Cr. Subsidised LPG connections<br />\r\nwherein, a major ratio of BPL families has been a dud on the grounds of this<br />\r\nscheme. It has observed that BPL families have claimed that they are unable to<br />\r\nafford LPG refills. <br />\r\nScheme Launched: for People Welfare or Votes Bagging? <br />\r\nHowever, the Ujjwala Scheme was launched for bagging of votes during elections<br />\r\nwith a promise that each rural woman of below poverty line household would be<br />\r\nfacilitated with the same but unfortunately, because of the high cost of LPG refills<br />\r\nthey saw a major dud. The strategy of acquiring the bulk votes was quite interesting<br />\r\nas it focussed on BPL household visits while sitting on the muddy floor and eating<br />\r\nthe meal cooked on the earthen stove or Chulhas. <br />\r\nHowever, to get the LPG cylinder under this scheme the BPL family woman required<br />\r\nto fill a form provided by the respective gas agency while paying the subsidized price<br />\r\nof ? 1750 otherwise without such scheme it would be costing ? 2950. <br />\r\nA Curse or A Cause<br />\r\nPeople of such families did enjoy the scheme until the time the cylinder doesn’t<br />\r\nrequire the refill. With the passing away of the gas, they again came back to the<br />\r\nChulhas using kerosene oil and other kinds of solid fuels. The emitted smoke from<br />\r\nsuch substances led to hazardous health issues. Moreover, as per the World Health<br />\r\nOrganisation, worldwide, 3.8 million people die because of the smoke exposure from<br />\r\nthe dirty stoves. Also, the stats obtained from WHO quoted that in India, 4,88,200<br />\r\ndeaths occur every year just because of the chronic obstructive pulmonary disease<br />\r\n(COPD), ischaemic heart disease, due to pneumonia, lung cancer, and stroke. Also,<br />\r\n8 complete years are lost amid 1,000 people majorly because of the indoor air<br />\r\npollution wherein, the most affected people are the children and the woman. <br />\r\nSaving Wealth or Losing Health <br />\r\nBoth the Indian societies as well as the government need to understand that cooking<br />\r\non Chulhas renders a huge number of fumes and smog which adversely affect the<br />\r\nenvironment then, how a human being can remain unaffected from the same? If,<br />\r\nUjjwala Scheme has been properly implemented focusing on the low cost of the gas<br />\r\nrefill then, it could have successfully helped the sufferers which they have been<br />\r\nfacing because of the constant use of Chulhas. <br />\r\nThe use of Chulhas adversely affects human health that it can cause a loss of vision,<br />\r\nlungs problem, inhaling or other breathing problems and a lot more than one can<br />\r\never imagine. For your safeguard, you need to take any action while not fully relying<br />\r\non government schemes. However, the government must support people with the<br />\r\nproper implementation of such schemes. It must organize the schemes that it may<br />\r\nnot affect the people for a shorter time span, in fact, help them in solving all their<br />\r\ndaily hurdles. <br />\r\nOne Initiative is Essential<br />\r\nThe people of such areas are out of the reach of a flourished money, so they feel<br />\r\nthemselves helpless. At least, one can be a light of help for them so that with one’s<br />\r\n<br />\r\ninitiative the entire society can be saved. Also, as per the government concerns, it<br />\r\nshould have set up the reasonable prices of gas refilling that people from Chulhas<br />\r\nmay move towards the LPG. This would surely bring a positive effect on society and<br />\r\nthe economy. <br />\r\nAgain, the concluded reason states that the unaffordability of LPG cylinders is the<br />\r\ncore concern of using Chulhas with the help of cow dung and coal that are easily<br />\r\naccessible. Else, in the fastest running era of the technology where Gas Stove is<br />\r\nbeing also replaced by the Electronic Induction, who wants to cook food on the<br />\r\nburning wood emitting fumes. The Government needs to reduce the prices of gas<br />\r\nrefilling that no house may remain left with the LPG cylinders. <br />\r\nPeople must also know the worth and importance of their health and time which is<br />\r\nbeing wasted sitting in front of Chulhas.',0,0,0,2000,2,'2019-12-03 12:27:01','2019-12-04 12:32:24'),(62,'5de7820f8d025',2,499,'Acid Attack','Public Awareness','Acid-Attack-From-Pain-To-Purpose.jpg','https://callupon.org/stba','Acid Attack - a Forceful Acceptance or Unwanted Rejection by the Society<br />\r\nVictims of Acid Attack are actually not the victims but the survivors in the society. But,<br />\r\nunfortunately, the people who do so on the bodies and faces of pretty and beautiful<br />\r\nladies require to cover their faces.<br />\r\nWhat would happen to snatch away the beauty of a beauty?<br />\r\nHere, the beauty of beauty means the beautiful physical appearance of a female which<br />\r\nsome societal monsters take away.<br />\r\nIndia has seen many cases and faces of acid attacks where the victims reveal both their<br />\r\ninner beauty and strength to accept the harsh reality of their reshaped physical<br />\r\nappearance. Alongside government, you need to take action withstanding strong at this<br />\r\nsocietal threat.<br />\r\nCases over Cases Revealing Victims<br />\r\nMake culture and society so strong that a woman can fearlessly cross a man outside<br />\r\nher home. There have been many victims such as<br />\r\nReshma Qureshi, who was just 17 years old, lost her vision. The saddest, harsh and<br />\r\nunacceptable reality is that her relatives and their friends collectively were involved in<br />\r\nthrowing acid on her face.<br />\r\nLakshmi Aggarwal, who was again a 17 years old girl, became a victim of a brutal acid<br />\r\nattack by her acquaintances.<br />\r\nDifferent Victims, Different Sufferings<br />\r\nWhereas, both the victims have their sufferings and pains but both of them have<br />\r\ninspired the society with their belief and strength. The mental trauma of losing your<br />\r\nnatural physical appearance haunts the most simultaneously the taunts of the society<br />\r\nand people passing by.<br />\r\nYes, not everyone rejects the victim of an acid attack but not everyone accepts them.<br />\r\nDeep inside the heart people always keep guilt and fear of untouchably and don’t<br />\r\naccept them.<br />\r\nUnanswerable Whys…<br />\r\nBut, the alarming question here is, why to throw acid on a face? Why haunt a person to<br />\r\nsuch an extent that without being in any malpractice they have to hide their face and<br />\r\nhave to ask for dignity? Why to forcefully feel pity for such victims where there are no<br />\r\n<br />\r\nflaws? There is ‘n’ number of Why(s) that both the society and governmental bodies<br />\r\nneed to answer.<br />\r\nSympathy or Empathy? Does inner beauty really matter or is just a matter of<br />\r\nwords?<br />\r\nMost of the time, people say that inner beauty, good heart, and hard work means<br />\r\neverything but deep inside, everyone goes beyond physical beauty and appearance.<br />\r\nThis is just to show the sympathy or a kind of show-off towards the victims of acid<br />\r\nattack.<br />\r\nThe bitter, as well as the harshest reality, is that society is cruel because when people<br />\r\ntaunt everyone on body shaming focusing on height, weight, health, complexion and<br />\r\nphysique then, acid attack is a big deal to tackle with.<br />\r\nSuch victims are not the culprits to be treated helpless in fact, why to make them a<br />\r\nvictim? When a person who gets targeted for an acid attack without even knowing, is<br />\r\nalso a human being. They haven’t lost the natural beauty of their own or accidentally.<br />\r\nThey face a loss of their face or body because of brutal planning by some societal<br />\r\nmonsters.<br />\r\nDignity is ALL Above<br />\r\nSuch people have equal rights to live in society as they used to live abreast with<br />\r\ncomplete dignity and respect. Also, instead of hiding your face and feeling ashamed,<br />\r\nyou should step ahead towards the culprits more strongly with gratitude that you are a<br />\r\nbeautiful creation of God and nothing can stop you doing all such stuff that you are fond<br />\r\nof.<br />\r\nDo not feel sorry instead live more of yourself without the guilt of not having beautiful<br />\r\nskin or face. Beauty is from the heart and inner beauty reflects from one\'s face and<br />\r\nthoughts because the face is the mirror of the heart.',0,0,0,2000,2,'2019-12-04 09:53:19','2019-12-04 15:29:00'),(63,'5de9e7fe751b5',6,500,'Onion Rates Spike','Price inflation','1235662_Wallpaper2.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbb','<p><strong>Onion’s Chopping Makes Eye Teary but Rising Rates of Onion have Seriously Made Citizens Cry </strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\nIndian people are left with the teary eyes because of the rising prices of the onion wherein, the prices have touched ?120-150 per kilo. Moreover, the prices are expected to soar more by the end of February 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Triggering of Unseasonable Rainfall led Crop Damage  </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The prices of onion have risen drastically in all over the country. The reason behind the rising cost is unseasonal rain as well as the shortage of onion crop. Also, the worst part is that the rising cost has not even benefited a single farmer instead they have complained that none of the onion crops has been fetched because of its poor quality. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Increasing Consumption led to Decreasing Requirements </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In accordance with some sophisticated sources, in India, the monthly consumption of onions was 15 lakh metric tons which shows a requirement of 50 thousand metric tons. But, with the high cost, the daily supply has become 10-12%, as of now. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Appeal to Government – a Solution for a Common Man</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most of the people and other associated welfare bodies have asked the government to create onion’s buffer stock, distribution of the staple at a reasonable cost, a crackdown on the hoarding of onion’s traders, etc just to relief a middle class and a common man. Onion as a staple of each kitchen in every household has affected not only the general public but a huge mass of farmers as well. Indian farmers have emotionally expressed a painful concern because most of them are distributing the old stock of onion because of the damaging of new onions. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just because the wholesale market has seen a huge spike in the cost, it has simultaneously affected the resulting market as well. Wherein, this sharper jump is restricting the public to make a hole in their pockets. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nationwide surge in the spike of onion price has affected most of the Indian states and cities such as Pune, Maharashtra, Chennai, Mumbai, Odisha, West Bengal, Kolkata, Delhi and a lot more. Therein, it has affected the market chain by affecting both the sellers and consumers in buying an onion. Nevertheless, daily consumers are unfortunately are forced to reduce their purchases and are cooking their delicious food as – onion free. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Battlefield between State & Central Government </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the other hand, the worst condition expressed by the farmers is the rotten onion which can neither be used nor purchased and can only get wasted by throwing and dumping it in the dustbins. Most of the citizens have appealed to the Central Government to take impactful immediate actions but, the tussle amid the state and the central government is affecting the common man, alas!!! </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Onion’s Robbery at Dusk’s Early Hours </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, the robbery of goods that can benefit you in any ground has been seen and observed in several different cases. But, have you ever heard of Onion’s robbery. Could you ever imagine that onions can also be getting stolen? Sounds funny; but, it’s true, 250kg onions worth ?2500 have been stolen from Gujarat vegetable shop during the early hours of dawn.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Government in Jitters & Public in Tears </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Such a looming onion crisis has put the government in jitters as well as the general public in tears. Therein, huge strata focussing on several households, cafes, and restaurants have been affected adversely. In short, this food inflation has made the entire nation cry where people are left with no choice just to maintain a cost-cutting for onion. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Indian Government must enlighten the issue and should immediately take the concern into consideration. This is because the continuous spike in the price is neither good for the country and nor for the Indian traders and farmers who are stagnantly witnessing a great fall in the onion demand.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Onion, with which every food tastes tasteless, is now getting reduced from the daily menus, dishes, and salads. However, to avoid the further disruption of the onion trade in the country, the government has placed orders for 6,090 tonnes of onions from Egypt to prevent India from Onion’s Crisis. This initiative would somewhere support the daily income of Indian farmers. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hope so, fresh and quality harvest may sooner hit the Indian market vanishing food inflation at its best.</p>\r\n',0,0,0,2000,2,'2019-12-06 05:32:46','2019-12-10 10:15:27'),(64,'5deb54cd11bd7',4,501,'Unemployment – A Constant Fear or Threat of Losing Job ','Social Reach','unemployment.jpeg','https://callupon.org/stbc','<strong>Unemployment – A Constant Fear or Threat of Losing Job </strong>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nPeople learn to earn and run their livelihood where learning doesn’t require any age or stage. Also, the process of learning begins with birth. Well, coming to the major use of learning in the Employment sector, it gets stopped at a certain level or gets restricted because of cost-cutting.\r\nSince, the downfalls in the GDP and other aspects of the Indian Economy, most of the employees have suffered and are still suffering the firing policies. Herein, the targeted employees are either the over-qualified people as per the company’s standards or the employees that are high salaried.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nMost of the organizations plan layoffs majorly for cost-cutting or due to the stagnant business strategies. Specifically talking about the private sector, employees always carry a mental trauma and fear or risk of losing their jobs because companies these days try to lay off approx. 5-8% of their entire workforce. </p>\r\n<strong>Why the Brain Drain? </strong>  \r\n<p> \r\nThis worst situation will also drown the country if the skill and talented mindsets would not be paid as per their qualifications, knowledge, and experience. This is also one of the major reasons for Brain Drain wherein, country and employment sectors should not have any authority to oppose and interfere. Just because, people both experienced and fresher do not get their demanded or wanted salary and become a victim of hire and fire hierarchy, seek for better opportunities in foreign countries. <p>   \r\n\r\n<p>    \r\nThey acquire and gain the knowledge fulfilling the criteria for any job role from India and work for other countries where their talent gets respect and they are paid as per their skills and knowledge. Here, the nation lacks much behind in terms of growth and development majorly focusing on employment. </P>   \r\n<p>   \r\nAlso, the ones who even doesn’t afford the good qualification and thus, do not get the jobs, work as vendors, auto-rickshaw or taxi drivers, work in café, tea stalls or restaurants and in fact, there is ‘n’ number of small scale professions. </p>   \r\n    \r\n<strong>Unemployment exists because of Cost-Cutting Strategies </strong>   \r\n<p>\r\nStreamlining cost has given birth to unemployment at a broader scale. On the other hand, coming to the government jobs, the competition is again too tough and stiff that a single vacancy for any of the designation requires the processing of 6-8 months. Most of the people from the age of 18 and above apply for the government vacancy with a hope that one day they may get a chance of having complete job security. Contradicting to this, again for a smaller number of vacancies, a huge number of people apply nationwide wherein, a few get a chance of selection.  <p>  \r\n    \r\n<strong>Employing the Unemployed has become an Occupation</strong>   \r\n<p>\r\nAlso, employing unemployed people has become a business. Most of the people play fraudulent activities with the name of branded organization and promise to unemployed ones providing a job with complete security. When a jobseeker gets influenced by the fraudsters, they ask for money. If a person gives the quoted amount then, these fraudsters run away leaving behind a no clue of their identification. </p>\r\n<p>    \r\nNo one knows where a nation will go if this would be continuing the way it is. Also, in the era of technology as well as digitalization, Information Technology (IT) domain is phasing the rough period of streamlining cost majorly concentrating on the employees of mid to senior level. Undoubtedly, this would further take the nation on the highest toll of unemployment in the next coming quarters. Owing to this, people tend and prefer to work in the UK, the US and other developed countries letting go of the Indian IT Sector and varied other sophisticated domains. </p>   \r\n    \r\n ',0,0,0,5000,1,'2019-12-07 07:29:17','2019-12-10 10:18:30'),(65,'5deb58e1e223c',2,502,'Priyanka Reddy’s Soul RIP whilst Accused Shot Dead by Hyderabad Police','The communalisation of rape by right-wing handles and outlet on social media','image.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbd','<p>On December 6, 2019, Hyderabad Police dead shot all 4 accused rapists and murders who took away the life of 26 years old Priyanka Reddy. The cops arrested all 4 named as Mohammad Ali alias Mohammad Arif, Jollu Shiva, Jollu Naveen Kumar, and Chintakunta Chenna Keshavulu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally today, the victim of brutal rape and murder got real and complete justice.  <strong>According to Police, all 4 accused have been killed in crossfire on Friday especially in the wee hours at the same highway where the burnt body of Priyanka was found. The accused were taken to the same spot and recreated the crime scene. All 4 tried to run and the moment they tried to flee, the IPS Office V.C Sajjanar IPS (Vishwanath Sajjanar) shot them. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As per the Hyderabad Police, the entire incident took place at 6:30 am. The purpose of encountering the accused in this way was the part of the investigation. Also, the accused forcefully snatched the guns from the police and fired on them and tried to escape from the site immediately. For safeguard and justice purposes, the police fired and shot them in which all 4 accused died. Also, as per the investigation from Hyderabad Police, the accused intentionally punctured the tire of Priyanka’s two-wheeler, offered her help, took her to hidden spot and brutally raped her. All the 4 accused were lorry workers and aged amid 20-25 age group. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Court’s Justice or Police’s Action</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This time not waiting for the court’s justice, Hyderabad Police took initiate on their own and supported the nation in the justice of Priyanka’s family. Till date, there is no hidden fact, that the accused of Delhi Gang Rape 2012 are still in jail and no punishment has been announced for them. The duration of 7 years is not short. If at that time, the court has taken a fair and immediate action and justice, no Priyanka could become the victim of a brutal rape and murder case again. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Hiring a Lawyer or helping them in running their livelihood</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People seek justice from the court but the Indian Judicial system just delays the cases giving dates over dates. A common man or a middle-class family affords a lawyer and a judge for the fair justice but, this has become a business to earn a livelihood now. Judicial bodies and systems do not understand the pain points of a common man instead of considering their money as their fees on the longer-term aspects which help them to earn and run their livelihood. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rapist Shot, Citizens Shocked</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This time, Hyderabad Police took action wherein, it was unbelievable for the citizens of the nation and simultaneously for the family members of a victim’s family. Was it Priyanka’s destiny or just was a furnished plan of the cops to give an answer to the nation for justice.? </p>\r\n<p>This time, immediate action has been taken while not hoping much from the judicial system. The nation is in the hope that no rape case may take place and no girl crossing on the road becomes a victim. This might also act as a lesson for the judicial system and other police officers as well that citizens seek their help for fair justice and not for the dates over dates on the grounds of court. </p>\r\n',0,0,0,2000,2,'2019-12-07 07:46:41','2019-12-10 10:20:06'),(66,'5def802f5fb3b',2,503,'Evoking Child Sex Abuse Provoking Gender Biasness ','Gender Biasness','nihms483449f2.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbe','<p>India is a country where civilization is worshipped above all priorities simultaneously abuses the sex of a child if it comes to know that the child is a girl. Does the launch of the campaign “Beti Bachao, Beti Padhao” seriously saving the girl child or have just taken for granted?</p> <br />\r\n<p>However, not every state in India prohibits or violates this yojana because awareness regarding the protection as well as education of girl child has immensely helped in improving the ratio of child sex abuse in the state like Haryana. Still, it\'s not just gotten restricted to Haryana because India needs much more improvement in the context of Girl Child. </p><br />\r\n<p>According to some renowned sources, going back to 2011 (eight years ago), in the district like Jhajjar, no one could ever imagine giving birth to a girl. Also, as per the 2011 Census, Jhajjar considered the worst district in terms of Child Sex Ratio and was also listed on the top as the worst-performing district. After Jhajjar, the district like Rewari and Kurukshetra came next in such context.</p> <br />\r\n<p>The country’s only motto is to lead its citizens with the great zeal towards each era including the girl child. Thus, it is mandatory to improve and promote gender equality wherein, since 2015, PM Narendra Modi’s launched Beti Bachao, Beti Padhao Yojana from Sonipat has a bit effected the people. </p><br />\r\n<p>Since the conceptualization as well as the launch of this campaign, awareness regarding education and protecting the girl child has been increased. But, only the initiative from the government’s ends or no other government policies would work until the people would start taking initiative on their own. </p><br />\r\n<p>Since 2019, according to the sources, it has seen that a CSR of 1,647:1000 is found in Dighal village wherein, it is doing much better in raising voice against child sex abuse in compliance with its other neighbouring villages.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Also, as per the societal point of view, still today there exists a lot of people whose mindsets have changed towards gender biases and gender equality. Not everyone is feminist and not everyone abuses child sex. Today’s present generation doesn’t find and judge anything wrong or exceptional in having a baby girl. This is because, in almost all fields today, ranging from personal to professional ones, girls dominate everywhere. </p><br />\r\n<p>On the other hand, still, the majority of the older generation believe in stereotypes and strive their best in resisting the present generation to have a girl over a boy. Somewhere somehow still the fact exists in the society that having a first baby as a girl people prefer to have a boy as a second. Slowly or sooner things need to change and that definitely would bring the best outcomes in the upcoming years. </p><br />\r\n<p>However, the fundamental purpose to launch Beti Bachao, Beti Padhao Yojana was to watch over the places and people who had involved themselves in the practices of using prenatal scanning or female infanticide to know the baby’s sex before his birth or within the female’s womb.</p> <br />\r\n<p>In addition to this, as per the press release of 2018’s state government, it has observed that the sex ratio is the year 2016 was 871 girls for 1,000 boys which improved to 900 girls per 1,000 boys in the year 2017. The number has been improvised because of the actions taken by the people such as FIRs against child sex abuse, awareness programs and raids at suspected ultrasound centres. </p><br />\r\n<p>Alongside the initiative taken by the local citizens, the state health department also acted as the watchdogs over the centres conducting prenatal sex determination tests. For more of the awareness, one strongly needs to educate every girl in his family with a core objective focusing on gender determination which is illegal and on sexual biases as well. Gender equality must be all above in all the eras of one\'s life. This is because a boy or a girl is one\'s personal choice to make but not a societal decision to adopt. </p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,1500,2,'2019-12-10 11:23:27','2019-12-12 09:57:58'),(67,'5df1c77db68a9',2,505,'India Nonexempt the Citizenship Prohibiting the Entry of Immigrants ','Nonexempt the Citizenship Prohibiting the Entry of Immigrants expose the social media','CitizenshipAmmendmentBill-356668401_8.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbf','<strong>India Nonexempt the Citizenship Prohibiting the Entry of Immigrants </strong><br />\r\n<p><br />\r\nOn December 11, 2019, the lower house of Indian parliament (Lok Sabha) passed a bill offering amnesty to Non-Muslim illegal migrants from 3 neighboring countries namely Pakistan, Bangladesh, and Afghanistan. Thus, the legislation has made it easier for Non-Muslim refugees to acquire citizenship. However, the legislation is only applicable to the people who arrived in India prior to December 31, 2014.</p><br />\r\n<strong>OCA Guidelines benefitting Foreigners</strong><br />\r\n<p><br />\r\nOn the other hand, the amendments have been also made to the provisions relating to Overseas Citizen of India (OCA) cardholders. Any foreigner is only allowed to register himself as an OCA falling under the guidelines of the 1955 Act. The act states that:</p><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<li> A person must be a former Indian citizen</li> <br />\r\n<li> Or the spouse of a person must be from India’s origin</li> <br />\r\n</ul><br />\r\n<p><br />\r\nFollowing such norms would help a foreigner in benefitting the right to travel to India including the work and study permit.  </p><br />\r\n<p><br />\r\nOn the contrary, the bill only amends the cancellation of OCI’s registration if any individual violates any law being notified by the central government of the country. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Muslims Marginalization</strong><br />\r\n<p>The government ruling party BJP says that the sanctuary will be given by the bill to the people who feel religious persecution. Therein, the opposition says that the bill has become a part of the ruling party’s agenda just to marginalize the Muslims. </p><br />\r\n<p>When it comes to the CAB i.e. Citizenship Amendment Bill, its passage has been considered as a test for the present ruling party in parliament’s upper house (Rajya Sabha) just because, therein, it lacks a majority. The bill has prompted a broader protest in the country’s northeastern borders, Bangladesh because people feel “overrun” by the cross border immigrants.</p><br />\r\n<strong>What does the bill state?</strong><br />\r\n<p> As per the amendments by CAB, the 64-year-old Indian Citizenship law completely prohibits the illegal migrants from becoming Indian citizens. The foreigner who enters in India without valid travel documents, visa and passport or stay beyond the permitted time are considered as illegal immigrants. They can be easily deported or jailed at any point in time. <br />\r\nAlso, as per the new amendments, a provision states that an individual must have stayed or worked in India at least for 11 years prior to applying for citizenship. However, exceptions are always omnipresent in somehow and somewhere situations and so herein, focusing on 6 religious minorities, they are the following: </p><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<li>Hindu</li><br />\r\n<li>Hindu</li><br />\r\n<li>Buddhist</li><br />\r\n<li>Jain</li><br />\r\n<li>Parsi</li><br />\r\n<li>Christian</li><br />\r\n</ul><br />\r\n<p>Only if, these 6 minorities can prove that they are from Pakistan, Afghanistan or Bangladesh then, they will have to work or live in India for 6 years so as to become eligible for citizenship via naturalization. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Naturalization is a process wherein, a non-citizen gains the nationality or citizenship of that country.</strong><br />\r\n<p>As the Indian constitution completely prohibits the religious discrimination against its citizens and guarantees equality for all the citizens in front of law thus, Naturalized citizenship is just an option for all those people who seek to claim the citizenship of India, legally.</p> ',0,0,0,2500,2,'2019-12-12 04:52:13','2019-12-13 13:23:49'),(68,'5df716db52486',8,20,'Marital Rape – a Non-Criminalized Crime or a Forceful Pleasure','Non-Criminalized Crime or a Forceful Pleasure.','marital_rape.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbg','<strong>Marital Rape – a Non-Criminalized Crime or a Forceful Pleasure </strong><br />\r\n<p>Is sex after marriage a romance or seriously a brutal rape? <br /><br />\r\nMarriage is a pretty beautiful relationship that withstands both on love and understanding. But, this also needs to be understood by the society that marriage is not only about physical love, sex or romance. If in any married relationship, without considering the tenure of the wedding, if your spouse especially your wife is not ready or prepared for physical love and you are forcing her to have that attention then, unfortunately, you are raping her, martially. </p><br />\r\n<strong>What Marital Rape states?</strong> <br />\r\n<p>To force a woman for physical love and attention without her permission in a marital relationship is known as Marital Rape. </p><br />\r\n<p>Talking about the Marital Rape, Narendra Modi’s government destabilizes the institution of marriage which could also act as a weapon to harass husbands. The government needs to understand and discover a stronger correlation amid saving the marriage institution as well as criminalizing marital rape. It’s a matter of concern that how difficult it could be getting a raped by a husband. From a societal point of view, this is not a big deal and is an obvious point but, for a female, this is nothing less than a brutal rape when she is not prepared and is not willing for physical love. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Just because you’re married so, forceful sex is okay</strong><br />\r\n<p>In India, there seem a lot of females who are a victim of the marital rape and continuously appeal for the justice but there is no hearing in the eyes of law, in the grounds of court and, in fact, in front of families. This is so because everyone seems that a couple is married so sex is official and is okay but, the concern gets over neglected that whether a person is willing or not without noticing that it’s a married couple. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Woman – a subject for sex, machine producing babies and idol of romance<strong><br />\r\n<p>Additionally, as per the societal point of view, in marital sex, a reasonable person is always a male wherein, a woman always ends up as a device of baby-making as well as an idol of romance. A typical marital rapist is the one who still believes that a woman can be ruled and dominated as per his will and choice. Also, he feels that in sexual matters if he wants sex then, she should be glad and if she isn’t then, a man has a complete right to force her. Overall this shows that he is an object and a lady is a sexual subject to play or mold with. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Feminism majorly exists in male dominating society</strong> <br />\r\n<p>Still today, the society is somewhere male-dominant where being feminist is not wrong. Thus, in such a male dominant society woman’s struggle is not only limited but reasonable as well. All man seriously needs to understand that a woman is not a sexual property. Marital rape is a crime that everyone including the government should need to understand and must enlighten the same very seriously.</p>',0,0,0,4500,3,'2019-12-16 05:32:11','2019-12-27 17:23:41'),(69,'5df7175861771',8,20,'Marital Rape – a Non-Criminalized Crime or a Forceful Pleasure','Non-Criminalized Crime or a Forceful Pleasure.','marital_rape.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbh','<strong>Marital Rape – a Non-Criminalized Crime or a Forceful Pleasure </strong><br />\r\n<p>Is sex after marriage a romance or seriously a brutal rape? <br /><br />\r\nMarriage is a pretty beautiful relationship that withstands both on love and understanding. But, this also needs to be understood by the society that marriage is not only about physical love, sex or romance. If in any married relationship, without considering the tenure of the wedding, if your spouse especially your wife is not ready or prepared for physical love and you are forcing her to have that attention then, unfortunately, you are raping her, martially. </p><br />\r\n<strong>What Marital Rape states?</strong> <br />\r\n<p>To force a woman for physical love and attention without her permission in a marital relationship is known as Marital Rape. </p><br />\r\n<p>Talking about the Marital Rape, Narendra Modi’s government destabilizes the institution of marriage which could also act as a weapon to harass husbands. The government needs to understand and discover a stronger correlation amid saving the marriage institution as well as criminalizing marital rape. It’s a matter of concern that how difficult it could be getting a raped by a husband. From a societal point of view, this is not a big deal and is an obvious point but, for a female, this is nothing less than a brutal rape when she is not prepared and is not willing for physical love. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Just because you’re married so, forceful sex is okay</strong><br />\r\n<p>In India, there seem a lot of females who are a victim of the marital rape and continuously appeal for the justice but there is no hearing in the eyes of law, in the grounds of court and, in fact, in front of families. This is so because everyone seems that a couple is married so sex is official and is okay but, the concern gets over neglected that whether a person is willing or not without noticing that it’s a married couple. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Woman – a subject for sex, machine producing babies and idol of romance</strong><br />\r\n<p>Additionally, as per the societal point of view, in marital sex, a reasonable person is always a male wherein, a woman always ends up as a device of baby-making as well as an idol of romance. A typical marital rapist is the one who still believes that a woman can be ruled and dominated as per his will and choice. Also, he feels that in sexual matters if he wants sex then, she should be glad and if she isn’t then, a man has a complete right to force her. Overall this shows that he is an object and a lady is a sexual subject to play or mold with. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Feminism majorly exists in male dominating society</strong> <br />\r\n<p>Still today, the society is somewhere male-dominant where being feminist is not wrong. Thus, in such a male dominant society woman’s struggle is not only limited but reasonable as well. All man seriously needs to understand that a woman is not a sexual property. Marital rape is a crime that everyone including the government should need to understand and must enlighten the same very seriously.</p><br />\r\n <br />\r\n ',0,0,0,3500,2,'2019-12-16 05:34:16','2019-12-20 11:34:54'),(70,'5df85e3e7357f',2,502,'Citizenship Amendment Act Triggered Violence at Jamia Millia Islamia University in Delhi','Citizenship Amendment Act Triggered violence Millia Islamia in social message','jamia-issue.jpeg','https://callupon.org/stbi','<strong>Citizenship Amendment Act Triggered Violence at Jamia Millia Islamia University<br />\r\nin Delhi</strong><br />\r\n<p>New Delhi’s well famous Muslim University named Jamia Millia Islamia University has<br />\r\nsuffered from a violent protest by the students against the amended bill of Citizenship.<br />\r\nApart from Jamia University, Aligarh’s famous Muslim University in Uttar Pradesh has<br />\r\nseen the same suffering due to the amendment of the Citizenship Act. The actions of<br />\r\npolice in AMU campuses and Jamia led more protests in many other places in UP, West<br />\r\nBengal, Bihar, and Telangana. However, Delhi’s campus remained the core center of<br />\r\nstudent’s protest.</p><br />\r\n<strong>6 Minorities from 3 Countries</strong><br />\r\n<p>As per the amended law, it gives the authority of acquiring the citizenships to the illegal<br />\r\nimmigrants who majorly belong to 6 religious minorities from 3 countries from<br />\r\nBangladesh, Pakistan, and Afghanistan excluding Muslims. The law has been relaxed<br />\r\nfor illegal migrants belonging to 6 categories such as Hindus, Sikhs, Buddhists, Jain,<br />\r\nParsi, and Christians.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Accusing Modi’s Government of targeting Hindutva</strong><br />\r\n<p>Excluding Muslims from the act has led many Muslim groups, opposition parties and<br />\r\nactivists to accuse the ruling government of targeting the Hindutva agenda. Also, the<br />\r\nprotest has taken place in Assam and many other parts of the Northeast. As per the<br />\r\nprotest, people called this amendment as unwarranted as well as the one which<br />\r\nthreatens the identity of social, economic and cultural morals.</p><br />\r\n<p>Before the amendment of the act under the law, the non-citizens were deported to their<br />\r\nnative or origin country. For any government, this could be a difficult task because no<br />\r\ncountry has accepted to those people who left out of NRC were nationals of Bangladesh<br />\r\nand Pakistan.</p><br />\r\n<p>Thus, this act has opened up new pathways for all the illegal immigrants abreast of all<br />\r\nthose who are declared as non-citizens under the Assam NRC. However, as per the<br />\r\nconcerns of Muslim immigrants, these pathways can’t be claimed under such an act.<br />\r\nTherefore, the illegal Muslim immigrants also the ones who had left out of the NRC have<br />\r\nan authority to appeal herein, non-Muslims have an option to apply for the acquisition of<br />\r\ncitizenship via a process of naturalization.</p><br />\r\n<strong>More Aggression, More Violence</strong><br />\r\n<p>This act has tremendously fuelled up the fear in varied leaders of the Muslim community<br />\r\nsaying that, a large amount of the Muslims would be declared as non-citizens. Also, in<br />\r\nthe amendment of the act, it has been claimed that the act was supposed to<br><br />\r\naccommodate people of other different communities for acquiring Indian citizenships<br />\r\nexcept for Muslims especially if they failed to prove themselves as India’s bona fide<br />\r\ncitizens. Owing to this, the high intensity of protests as well as violence found out to be<br />\r\nrising with a much more alarming rate abreast with more of the fear, anger or<br />\r\naggression.</p><br />\r\n<p>Moreover, the act was passed by the Indian Parliament, last week stating that it may not<br />\r\napply to all those people who have been left out of the nationwide NRC.</p>',0,0,0,2500,3,'2019-12-17 04:49:02','2019-12-27 17:23:34'),(71,'5df8614ecb9c1',2,502,'Citizenship Amendment Act Triggered Violence at Jamia Millia Islamia University in Delhi','Citizenship Amendment Act Triggered violence Millia Islamia in social message','jamia.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbj','<strong>Citizenship Amendment Act Triggered Violence at Jamia Millia Islamia University<br />\r\nin Delhi</strong><br />\r\n<p>New Delhi’s well famous Muslim University named Jamia Millia Islamia University has<br />\r\nsuffered from a violent protest by the students against the amended bill of Citizenship.<br />\r\nApart from Jamia University, Aligarh’s famous Muslim University in Uttar Pradesh has<br />\r\nseen the same suffering due to the amendment of the Citizenship Act. The actions of<br />\r\npolice in AMU campuses and Jamia led more protests in many other places in UP, West<br />\r\nBengal, Bihar, and Telangana. However, Delhi’s campus remained the core center of<br />\r\nstudent’s protest.</p><br />\r\n<strong>6 Minorities from 3 Countries</strong><br />\r\n<p>As per the amended law, it gives the authority of acquiring the citizenships to the illegal<br />\r\nimmigrants who majorly belong to 6 religious minorities from 3 countries from<br />\r\nBangladesh, Pakistan, and Afghanistan excluding Muslims. The law has been relaxed<br />\r\nfor illegal migrants belonging to 6 categories such as Hindus, Sikhs, Buddhists, Jain,<br />\r\nParsi, and Christians.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Accusing Modi’s Government of targeting Hindutva</strong><br />\r\n<p>Excluding Muslims from the act has led many Muslim groups, opposition parties and<br />\r\nactivists to accuse the ruling government of targeting the Hindutva agenda. Also, the<br />\r\nprotest has taken place in Assam and many other parts of the Northeast. As per the<br />\r\nprotest, people called this amendment as unwarranted as well as the one which<br />\r\nthreatens the identity of social, economic and cultural morals.</p><br />\r\n<p>Before the amendment of the act under the law, the non-citizens were deported to their<br />\r\nnative or origin country. For any government, this could be a difficult task because no<br />\r\ncountry has accepted to those people who left out of NRC were nationals of Bangladesh<br />\r\nand Pakistan.</p><br />\r\n<p>Thus, this act has opened up new pathways for all the illegal immigrants abreast of all<br />\r\nthose who are declared as non-citizens under the Assam NRC. However, as per the<br />\r\nconcerns of Muslim immigrants, these pathways can’t be claimed under such an act.<br />\r\nTherefore, the illegal Muslim immigrants also the ones who had left out of the NRC have<br />\r\nan authority to appeal herein, non-Muslims have an option to apply for the acquisition of<br />\r\ncitizenship via a process of naturalization.</p><br />\r\n<strong>More Aggression, More Violence</strong><br />\r\n<p>This act has tremendously fuelled up the fear in varied leaders of the Muslim community<br />\r\nsaying that, a large amount of the Muslims would be declared as non-citizens. Also, in<br />\r\nthe amendment of the act, it has been claimed that the act was supposed to<br><br />\r\naccommodate people of other different communities for acquiring Indian citizenships<br />\r\nexcept for Muslims especially if they failed to prove themselves as India’s bona fide<br />\r\ncitizens. Owing to this, the high intensity of protests as well as violence found out to be<br />\r\nrising with a much more alarming rate abreast with more of the fear, anger or<br />\r\naggression.</p><br />\r\n<p>Moreover, the act was passed by the Indian Parliament, last week stating that it may not<br />\r\napply to all those people who have been left out of the nationwide NRC.</p>',0,0,0,2200,2,'2019-12-17 05:02:06','2019-12-20 11:34:12'),(72,'5df9b36b39de8',2,21,'Illegal Surveillance couldn’t be led by any legal oversight','Illegal Surveillance couldn\'t be led by any legal oversight on social media ','NYPD-Surveillance.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbk','<strong>Illegal Surveillance couldn’t be led by any legal oversight</strong><br />\r\n<p>It is true that change always brings a transformation wherein, some people accept it and some protests for it. However, protests and violence for any change happening in the nation have become common and there is nothing new in it. But, somewhere somehow it has to take a form of adversarial tactics from different States.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Cops Comprising Facial Recognition Units</strong><br />\r\n<p>With the brutal protests in Jamia Millia Islamia University based in New Delhi, the reports have been found with the national security agencies as well as the with the cops using CCTVs video and facial recognition identifying all the protesting people. Police agencies such as Hyderabad Police, Delhi Police, and Surat Police are some departments that comprise of the facial recognition units. This face recognition has been primarily done in identifying people in criminal databases of the police department making use of the CCTNS. This majorly stands for Crime and Criminal Tracking Network and Systems.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Different Information from Different Government Departments</strong><br />\r\n<p>However, via the National Crime Records Bureau, such kind of system has been envisioned. Additionally, a tender for National Automated Facial Recognition System has been also issued by NCRB which would be considered as a part of CCTNS. Thus, in order to build and establish a good database for the police to monitor, it has been planned by NCRB to collect varied information for different governmental bodies and departments as well. Thus, the system has extended itself at its best to analyze and track all kinds of sexual offenders making use of the data of the facial recognition majorly belonging from the registry of national sexual offenders.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Students Facing Tear Gas</strong><br />\r\n<p>With the protest taking place in most of the parts of the nation, the states are doing its premium by clamping on all the aggressive and innocent people who have been a part of the protest. Ranging from the brutal killing of the teens majorly in the north-east, the students have been also faced by the tear gas wherein, the Indian police force is also acting persistently beyond their operating processes. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Protests – a symbol of Democracy or Violence</strong><br />\r\n<p>As per Article 19(1)(b) of the India Constitution, the right peaceful assembly and procession have been equally guaranteed to all the citizens of the nation. Coming to the protests, it has been described as a symbol of democracy in the country which allows its citizens to express their agency with their residing state on acting upon different things. Perhaps, facial recognition can indeed be helpful to an extent wherein, the police don’t have a right to use facial recognition without an ordered of the surveillance law by the Supreme Court.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Anti-Social is a Taboo</strong><br />\r\n<p> The in the process of being anti-social getting a taboo in the society, the state as well as its associated agents do not have any authority to branding someone when the protestor’s identity is unknown. Worldwide, there exist a lot of people who are completely in the process of facial recognition. But, on the contrary, in a country like India, neither the process of face recognition has been banned nor it is becoming a source of a meaningful piece of information for the country’s citizens. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Saying is Easy than Proving</strong><br />\r\n<p>Last but not the least; anyone can easily say that the Indian Police Department might be doing this everywhere but the fact is that most of the experiments have been carried out all across the nation regarding this process affecting everyone somewhere somehow. If anyone of us is in a favor of facial recognition and supports the CCTVs then, it must be the demand of the body cameras for the cops in order to prevent and stop the brutal actions against the innocent protestors at that same point in time. </p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,1800,2,'2019-12-18 05:04:43','2019-12-18 12:12:23'),(73,'5dfc611bee2f1',2,502,'Curbing Traffic between Protests: Huge Traffic Jam at Delhi – Gurugram Border','Curbing Traffic between Protests ','Delhi-traffic.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbl','<strong>Curbing Traffic between Protests: Huge Traffic Jam at Delhi – Gurugram Border</strong><br />\r\n<p>Nation’s alarming violence has brutally disturbed everyone that people now feel afraid of stepping out of their house. This persistently occurring violence has generated a serious atmosphere in the societies leading awe in the heart and minds of people.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Curbing Violence Affecting Commuters</strong><br />\r\n<p>Coming to the commuters in Delhi Metro, people are facing difficulties in daily traveling because most of the metro stations are closed due to the curbing violence. Not only the DMRC & NMRC instead most of the roads are also suffering from a huge traffic jam. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Where would our Nation go if the situation continues to go? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Massive Jam has been witnessed in major parts of the Delhi NCR with a specific focus on Gurugram. In order to clamp down the protests against the amended act of citizenship, the authorities have imposed traffic restrictions, barricaded roads as well as also suspended Internet services. Therein, the Delhi-Gurugram border was the worst affected point on Thursday, December 19. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Section 144 Implemented</strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, the threatening or say the alerting part for the National Capital Region is that, the cops have also imposed a ban on huge gatherings under Section 144 of the CrPC in central Delhi near Red Fort. Moreover, the police are inspecting each and every passing car entering into the city whilst assuring that the people, as well as the opposition parties, might plan to join certain allegations to hurt, harm or threaten people. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Traffic Movements – Commuters Revolution </strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, the operator services have been also suspended majorly by Vodafone and Airtel wherein, no voice, messages and internet services would be available in certain areas of Delhi. As per the cops, it has been also announced that the route of Mathura Road connecting to Kalindi Kunj has been closed for the traffic movements. Also, NCR’s commuters have been told to enter Delhi from Noida and vice versa via DND Flyway or the Akshardham road. Additionally, entry and exit gates of 20 metro stations have been shut down for security purposes. </p><br />\r\n<p>On the other hand, an alert has been also issued by the Gurugram Traffic Police stating about the traffic congestion arising out of 8 different borders connecting with Delhi being sealed. Since the amendment of the citizenship act, the protest, as well as violence, is persistently taking place more in the areas of Northeast, West Bengal and Delhi.</p><br />\r\n<strong>What, Why & Who is waiting for Whom? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Well, who would take an action or initiative to calm down the aggression of the Indian citizens? Is this a planning of the ruling parties or a strategy of sympathy gaining from anti-Muslims? Now, this is the high time for the nation to get united. Instead of blaming each other, killing people, burning buses, generating violence, lathi charge, rallies, blocking traffic, roads and public transports including other modes of commuting such as metro and flights, nothing would work. As a result, it is the citizens of the nation irrespective of the gender, caste, and religion who have to suffer the pain and the loss Alas!!! </p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,3000,2,'2019-12-20 05:50:19','2019-12-20 11:32:50'),(74,'5dfc611e31101',2,502,'Curbing Traffic between Protests: Huge Traffic Jam at Delhi – Gurugram Border','Curbing Traffic between Protests ','Delhi-traffic.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbm','<strong>Curbing Traffic between Protests: Huge Traffic Jam at Delhi – Gurugram Border</strong><br />\r\n<p>Nation’s alarming violence has brutally disturbed everyone that people now feel afraid of stepping out of their house. This persistently occurring violence has generated a serious atmosphere in the societies leading awe in the heart and minds of people.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Curbing Violence Affecting Commuters</strong><br />\r\n<p>Coming to the commuters in Delhi Metro, people are facing difficulties in daily traveling because most of the metro stations are closed due to the curbing violence. Not only the DMRC & NMRC instead most of the roads are also suffering from a huge traffic jam. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Where would our Nation go if the situation continues to go? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Massive Jam has been witnessed in major parts of the Delhi NCR with a specific focus on Gurugram. In order to clamp down the protests against the amended act of citizenship, the authorities have imposed traffic restrictions, barricaded roads as well as also suspended Internet services. Therein, the Delhi-Gurugram border was the worst affected point on Thursday, December 19. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Section 144 Implemented</strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, the threatening or say the alerting part for the National Capital Region is that, the cops have also imposed a ban on huge gatherings under Section 144 of the CrPC in central Delhi near Red Fort. Moreover, the police are inspecting each and every passing car entering into the city whilst assuring that the people, as well as the opposition parties, might plan to join certain allegations to hurt, harm or threaten people. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Traffic Movements – Commuters Revolution </strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, the operator services have been also suspended majorly by Vodafone and Airtel wherein, no voice, messages and internet services would be available in certain areas of Delhi. As per the cops, it has been also announced that the route of Mathura Road connecting to Kalindi Kunj has been closed for the traffic movements. Also, NCR’s commuters have been told to enter Delhi from Noida and vice versa via DND Flyway or the Akshardham road. Additionally, entry and exit gates of 20 metro stations have been shut down for security purposes. </p><br />\r\n<p>On the other hand, an alert has been also issued by the Gurugram Traffic Police stating about the traffic congestion arising out of 8 different borders connecting with Delhi being sealed. Since the amendment of the citizenship act, the protest, as well as violence, is persistently taking place more in the areas of Northeast, West Bengal and Delhi.</p><br />\r\n<strong>What, Why & Who is waiting for Whom? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Well, who would take an action or initiative to calm down the aggression of the Indian citizens? Is this a planning of the ruling parties or a strategy of sympathy gaining from anti-Muslims? Now, this is the high time for the nation to get united. Instead of blaming each other, killing people, burning buses, generating violence, lathi charge, rallies, blocking traffic, roads and public transports including other modes of commuting such as metro and flights, nothing would work. As a result, it is the citizens of the nation irrespective of the gender, caste, and religion who have to suffer the pain and the loss Alas!!! </p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,3000,3,'2019-12-20 05:50:22','2019-12-27 17:23:28'),(75,'5e05fcb79c04a',7,502,'A Salute to Ragpickers: Living Unhygienically, Serving Hygiene',' Living Unhygienically, Serving Hygiene','gettyimages.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbn','<strong>A Salute to Ragpickers: Living Unhygienically, Serving Hygiene </strong><br />\r\n<p>It is often and easy to find a large number of the children at the Deonar dumping ground, who live and grow in the pools of garbage since their childhood.</p> <br />\r\n<p>People move to urban or metropolitan cities from their undeveloped or rural areas in the hope of getting a better life, health and wealth. Therein, with hardly any employment opportunities, they strive to struggle to earn and run their livelihood. Barely, they are in strata of hand to mouth at least once in a day. Such people do not hope for the riches instead feel pleasure enough just to get a single daily meal. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Life as a Ragpickers </strong><br />\r\n<p>Today in the scanty world of work, such people hardly earn ? 150-200 regularly. Living in the darkest night with a hope of no positive sunrise, one-room muddy or kachcha house, people have become completely hopeless seeking the hope of having a better and normal life. </p><br />\r\n<p>Segregating the garbage on the outskirts of the roads and removing tons of garbage daily, these people have become acquainted with several hazardous diseases. Also, there is no hidden fact that garbage has no shape, size, and form. It can be anything and anywhere recyclable and on-recyclable as well. Picking and segregating the garbage, Ragpickers often sustain cuts majorly when the garbage seems of metal, glass or any other form leading to cuts at the skin. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Poor Quality Life with Alcoholism</strong><br />\r\n<p>Ragpicker\'s pain is too deep and immense to apprehend. Females who pick garbage and earn some penny, their spouse blow all that money into drugs and alcoholism. Whatever money they earn, the husbands of such females pass it away in drinking alcohol. </p><br />\r\n<p>Their body has become so immune that no disease is hidden from them. They have been working amid the garbage since their childhood that hygiene becomes uneasy for them to digest. Indeed, there are a large number of children who grow up in the garbage wherein, the unregulated industry of child Ragpickers is growing ridiculously and speedily as well.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>What should government regulatory bodies do?</strong><br />\r\n<p> Launching health regulatory policies and hygiene or maintaining cleanliness policies is very easy to announce and launch. But, the real effect is seen when it comes to implementation. Government makes well promises to give a healthy and wealthy life to Ragpickers with much betterment but the hash and unacceptable truth are that their life has only become worsened. The only irony is that the abundance of such hopes is given before the election.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,2000,2,'2019-12-27 12:44:39','2019-12-30 18:31:20'),(76,'5e05ffd103b49',2,502,'Still, after independence, has India become Independent or is a slave of riots & malpractice?',' slave of riots & malpractice','WWP005.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbo','<strong>Still, after independence, has India become Independent or is a slave of riots & malpractice?</strong><br />\r\n<p>Being a democratic country, still today, India is facing ‘n’ number of political issues on an almost regular basis wherein, some come into existence, some get highlighted and some remain hidden from the societal point of view. Talking about the major societal concerns such as elections, employment focusing on both public and private sector, reservation and these days “the citizenship act”, most of the concerns has brutally disturbed the society from its core. </p><br />\r\n<strong>India – Democratic & Secular Country</strong><br />\r\n<p>India being a secular & democratic country gives complete right to worship anyone and choose the religion of citizen’s choice. It seems like, with such alarming as well as the threatening concerns, issues generating riots amid the citizens are found to be at its peak.<br><br />\r\nBeing the citizens of the nation, it would be much recommendable that people must build a community to predict the future. One major and common issue which is always considered as the constant is the Hindu Muslim Riots and Slogans. Each and every time we come across listening to the slogans raised against Hindu and Muslim communities, Hindustan and Pakistan. Movies like Bajrangi Bhaijaan can’t work or unite humanity especially when it comes to the Hindu and Muslims.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Are we united or still separated living in a nation?  </strong><br />\r\n<p>Why this differentiation is still present even after getting independent? Aren’t we the citizen of one nation? In bringing forth such togetherness, NO <br> <br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n    <li>    Government</li><br />\r\n    <li>    Policies</li><br />\r\n    <li>    Movies</li><br />\r\n</ul><br />\r\ncan unite such communities instead of the people’s initiative belonging to such communities. However, all such above mentioned components can just inspire us for a few minutes and seconds but the feeling of togetherness will be generated from our self. </p><br />\r\n<p>Before becoming a Hindu or a Muslim, be a Human 1st. <br><br />\r\nRiots and issues are many which even cannot be counted on fingers. A list will also fall apart if one counts the issues between the differences.</p><br />\r\n<p>Dear People, it’s time to get amalgamate, we can’t do anything instead of loving each other, getting involved in each other’s happiness and togetherness. This is so because this feeling of being one’s enemy serves the politicians in a large amount of the malpractices. The leading politicians belonging to both the parties are taking the huger advantages in filling their pockets with the bulk cash while not fulfilling the manifestos as promised especially during the time of an election. </p><br />\r\n<p>So, be united to see unity in the system. It doesn’t matter that a Hindu or a Muslim is running a nation or is an MLA. Alas! It\'s we only who have to suffer and no one will be affected by such issues and concerns. Slogans like <strong>“Hindu Muslim Sikh Ishai, apas mei sab Bhai Bhai”</strong> would no longer work until and unless we implement it on our personal life and ideologies. </p> <br />\r\n <br />\r\n ',0,0,0,2500,2,'2019-12-27 12:57:53','2019-12-30 18:31:16'),(77,'5e09ed8a86bb6',3,505,'Exam’s Stress: Leading Anxiety Snatching Sleep','Leading Anxiety Snatching Sleep','Stressjpeg.jpeg','https://callupon.org/stbp','<strong>Exam’s Stress: Leading Anxiety Snatching Sleep</strong><br />\r\n<p>Well, with the time appearing close to exams especially focusing on Boards<br />\r\nExaminations, the stress amid the students if found at the height beyond peak. This<br />\r\nstress majorly defines the fear of getting good marks or to top in the subjects,<br />\r\nadmissions in good colleges or university, societal pressure and there are ‘n&#39; number of<br />\r\nreasons associated with the career objective of the students. Such anxiety leads<br />\r\nstudents towards insomnia, sleep disorders and different forms of sleep paralysis.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Natural Sleep is replaced with Insomnia </strong><br />\r\n<p>The situation of insomnia is becoming so drastic that instead of having a natural sound<br />\r\nsleep of at least 8 hours, students are shifting towards the sleeping pills. In fact, with the<br />\r\ncontinuous demand as prescribed by the students, the platforms distributing such<br />\r\nservices are continuously selling such products amid the market abreast with its over-<br />\r\nthe-counter distribution. However, the sellers sell these pills with a promise that the<br />\r\ndrugs are scientifically proven and tested that aims in improving the body’s<br />\r\nperformance.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Everyone has their own buckets of problems</strong><br />\r\n<p>It is true that presently, the world is filled with a large number of people who are<br />\r\nsuffering from anxiety and insomnia with ‘n’ number of reasons. However, the reasons<br />\r\nbehind such sickness is that because of unhealthy eating habits as well as poor<br />\r\nstandards of living, people all over the world are suffering from sickness like anything. </p><br />\r\n<strong> Disorder turns into a Disease </strong><br />\r\n<p>Therein, people considering and consuming sleeping pills feel that they get relief but,<br />\r\nthere is also a hidden fact associated that they are destroying their life by themselves.<br />\r\nThey consider sleeping pills as the best aid for short-term insomnia treatment including<br />\r\nanxiety disorders. Undoubtedly, a person consuming such pills gets introduced with a<br />\r\nperfectly sound sleep abreast with no disturbances. But, the worst truth is that they are<br />\r\nlosing the natural sound sleep. The sub-conscious mind becomes so habitual to such<br />\r\npills that not having a natural sleep again becomes a disorder turning to disease. Thus,<br />\r\npeople considering such drugs as the best aid for the sufferers of anxiety and<br />\r\nsleeplessness are accepting the myth. </p><br />\r\n<strong>GABA: The Chemical Messenger</strong><br />\r\n</p>Sleeping pills and drugs as well as other benzodiazepines, act with an enhancement of<br />\r\nthe gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) directly inside the brain. Fundamentally, GABA is<br />\r\na neurotransmitter that easily inhibits almost all the activities of the brain. It also<br />\r\nbecomes mandatory to know that GABA receptors are the chemical messenger used by<br />\r\nthe nerve cells in order to easily communicate with each other. <br><br />\r\nIf you are in a need of a treatment via which you may easily fall asleep then, meditation,<br />\r\neasy and healthy standard of living and other natural aids that take away the stress is<br />\r\nwhat the best doorway towards the same despite consumption of sleeping pills.<br><br />\r\nThe government of the nation must also focus on such easy availability of the drug<br />\r\neither online or over-the-counter at cost-effective prices while depriving of the discounts<br />\r\noffer. <br><br />\r\nThis is so because, if people would start preferring or consuming sleeping pills or<br />\r\nanother form of drugs rendering sleep and solving anxiety for short-term would surely<br />\r\npull them in a pool of diseases and other hilarious disorders.</p>',0,0,0,3000,2,'2019-12-30 12:28:58','2019-12-30 18:31:00'),(78,'5e156908cbddf',7,21,'Plastic Revolution led Plastic Free India: Green India, Clean India','Plastic Revolution led Plastic Free India , Become my country is Green India','plastics.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbq','<strong>Plastic Revolution led Plastic Free India: Green India, Clean India</strong><br />\r\n<p>A massive campaign for Plastic-Free India has been initiated wherein; the same had been informed to UNGA by PM Modi. Since a longer duration, the country has been witnessing the elimination of single-use plastic for which, the Prime Minister of India has used varied forms of the reckoned international platforms for its emphasis focusing more on the banning of the product.</p> <br />\r\n<p>He implemented a gigantic campaign informing the world that the country initiated a plastic-free campaign for a purpose of giving a clearer direction to the country in getting free from plastic and introduced nation as a worldwide plastic-free nation. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Never-Ending Plastic… </strong><br />\r\n<p>It’s common as well as a well-known fact that the plastic can never be destroyed nor can be decomposed. But, on the other hand, how much can it destroy the environment is beyond an individual’s thinking capacity to think. Therefore, to represent and introduce India as free from plastic, PM Modi had been addressed in the New York’s 74th session of the United Nations General Assembly. </p><br />\r\n<p>The Campaign has been greatly welcomed and must be welcomed by the Indian citizens as it’s we only who have to make India a plastic banned country. Simultaneously, the fact must be immensely respected that, after the launching of a huge campaign, people wholeheartedly accepted this and showed their efforts in making a country a healthy and wise country. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Concerns for Sustainable Nation</strong><br />\r\n<p>Therefore, during the Biarritz’s G7 Summit, most of the interesting, curious and fundamental efforts have been highlighted focusing on different issues that can collaboratively build the health of the nations. The issues that were taken more into the consideration were: Wildlife Protection, Forest Reservation, Sustainable Development, Ecological Balance, Protection of Flora & Fauna, Water Conservation and Reservation, Renewable and Non-Renewable Resources, Harassment of Solar Energy and much more for the safeguard of a healthy environment as well as sustainable future. </p><br />\r\n<strong>India needs a right direction to be HEALTHY </strong><br />\r\n<p>As per the concerns of India’s Environment Ministry, approximately, 20,000 tons of plastic waste is found to be generated every day. Out of the 20,000 tons approx. 13-14000 tons get collected and rest either remains scattered on the roads or remained alive in the sea, river or ponds. Herein, a problem comes into consideration that after implementation of such a huge campaign in all over India, still a huge amount of the plastic wastes are found either scattered or dumped at certain places. Such form of an inadequate collection including ‘n’ numbers of the recycling systems, India needs the right direction to be a healthy and wealthy nation or to be called a plastic-free nation in real-sense.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Plastic Revolution: A Serious Revolution </strong><br />\r\n<p>A serious revolution is required amid the people living in the nation while getting influenced by Plastic Revolution for a plastic-free nation. Therein, it had been strongly appealed by the constructors, builders and varied shopkeepers to recycle plastic wherever possible and start providing goods in paper or cloth bags instead of the plastic ones.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Also, the nation is requested to make a shout out in saying goodbye to the plastic urging citizens to curb the use of the same. Thus, saying goodbye isn’t sufficient it is also required to ban all kinds of the small and tiny plastics focusing on plastic carry bags, artificial banners, thermocol disposable cutlery, flags and flowers, plastic folders and water bottles, food packaging, bottles, straws, containers, cups, etc.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,4500,2,'2020-01-08 05:30:48','2020-01-08 12:48:29'),(79,'5e180e5348783',3,505,'A Workplace… Does it Seriously a Workplace or a Place of Bullying People???','Seriously a Workplace or a Place of Bullying People Stress on Workspace','work-argument.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbr','<strong>A Workplace… Does it Seriously a Workplace or a Place of Bullying People???</strong><br />\r\n<p>A workplace where everyone is welcomed to work based on their qualifications and experience and irrespective of gender, caste, and race. When all such factors are mandatory to be fulfilled in a corporate then, why people get bully at certain levels because of the aging? They too have a right to work as per their choice and would definitely get retired based on the policies and norms of any industry. <br><br />\r\nThen, why people get criticized for aging specifically in the corporate having the youth and youngster?</p><br />\r\n<p>The fact is clear and apparent that age discrimination is against the law due to the assumed or actual age. Also, every employee is protected from age discrimination concerns at all the employment’s stages often including dismissal, recruitment as well as the terms and conditions of the workplace. It is true that assumptions and stereotypes regarding the young people and mature workers could leave a major influence on their vie points pertaining to decisions and other concerns.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Alongside this, it is also important to enlighten the major factors that must be taken into consideration whilst focusing on Age Discrimination such as: </p><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<li>•    Someone’s personal advertising and branding pertaining to its personality and physical appearance</li><br />\r\n<li>•    Hailing people as a young and dynamic team </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Not attending and treating a candidate during the interview because either they are too old or too young for the organization </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Not employing the teenagers especially fresher with a mindset that they will leave the organization </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Similarly, not employing the mature workers again with a mindset that they will get the earliest retirement</li><br />\r\n<li>•    Choices and decisions against provoking, encouraging and forcing someone to retire or to leave because of their age factors</li><br />\r\n</ul><br />\r\n<strong>Organizational Positive Roles & Responsibilities </strong><br />\r\n<p>Being an employer of a sophisticated organization, there must not be any biasness in terms of decision-making systems and thus, a rational decision should be announced with no emotional feelings and emotions. The reasonable measures must be taken into consideration to prevent age discrimination including other happening factors like health, weight, height, complexion, caste, and creed. If an organization follows such kind of positive attitude towards its employees then, surely it would be growing and leading itself towards gratitude and also called “positive duty”.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Therefore, an employer is required to always take the proactive actions herein, proactive actions mostly means interview screening and scheduling, work culture and environment, recruitment and retirement, on-time salaries, harassment, leave policies specifically for pregnant or lactating woman and there are ‘n’ number of policies, terms, and conditions that both the employer and employee should consider and follow. If such policies would be addressed positively, formally and in a wealthy way then, undoubtedly organization and its employees will grow simultaneously.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Last but not least, most of the time, discrimination has been observed in mature age workers. Unfortunately, the discrimination amid them is extremely widespread. Owing to such discriminations, the complain while applying for jobs and new opportunities. They are overlooked, mistreated and ignored just because they are too mature especially when it comes to promotion and increment.</p>  <br />\r\n<p>Thus, employers are liable for their employee’s acts of harassment and discrimination. Therein, they also have a positive duty in eliminating such harassment and age discrimination pertaining to any reliable factor they feel absolutely unfair.</p> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,4000,1,'2020-01-10 05:40:35','2020-01-10 11:10:35'),(80,'5e1c42a019d30',4,502,'Does Employee Motivation is a stack of only Financial Rewards or is something more?','Employee Motivation is a stack of only Financial Rewards','motivate_image.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbs','<strong>Does Employee Motivation is a stack of only Financial Rewards or is something more?</strong><br />\r\n<p>In developing approaches to motivate employees, managers focus mainly on financial rewards.<br/> <br />\r\nUndoubtedly, motivated employees are the key successful path both for the growth and development of an organization. In fact, it is natural that an organization is motivated only with its motivated employees. In the hustle bustle of the competitive era where everyone is a player to win the organizational race, managers of the firm must focus both on the financial rewards and employees motivation as well. </p><br />\r\n<p>However, sometimes employee’s motivation using rewards becomes intimidating for the managers. This should not happen because when your work culture is armed with the correct and appropriate information and tactics then why would managers feel daunt in enhancing the motivation of his employees using rewards in no time. The managers who always develop and revamp the employee rewards program must concentrate on some of the most mandatory aspects. </p><br />\r\n<strong>This article would tell you in brief… </strong><br />\r\n<p>Employees Involvement in the implementation of a rewards program would work better because this would encourage them interacting amid all the staff no matter senior or junior. Doing so would also ensure that the upper management including all the employees is on board with the organization’s reward system.</p> <br />\r\n<p>On the contrary, it should be noticeable that employee’s involvement in such programs is a worthy effort. The managers must always value the inputs provided by them irrespective of their designation, experience and age and then, select rewards accordingly. Owing to this, the employees who see worthy efforts in rewards will always feel motivated and would often act proactively.</p> <br />\r\n<p>It’s also important on the part of managers to assure that how employees can also comprehend to earn rewards. Involving them in the programs and valuing their inputs must not be restricted. However, managers should clearly explain to them how they can earn rewards. This is because, when your employees would be having a transparent understanding of expectations then, they will be capable enough of achieving the same. <br/><br />\r\nOn the contrary, employees must also establish transparent and reasonable performance standards to achieve rewards. This would lead them to engage the necessary efforts as expected or sometimes beyond expectations. Thus, managers must check in with the employees assuring that the rewards are near to their reach. Additionally, assisting the employees with a relevant dashboard via which they could observe their daily, weekly or monthly performance in real-time as per their assigned task. This is because; this would also allow them to have proper access to their tasks and performances in order to have realistic expectations for the expected rewards. </p><br />\r\n<p> Also, it\'s genuine on the manager’s part which employees should also understand that rewards are always based on the determination of the objective performance data. This is because, when the rewards get served based on the same then, more likely, employees feel no biases in the process and generate a right understanding of what is expected from them. Unbiased or fair judgment always fills employees with great motivation, enthusiasm, passion, and zeal towards the work. </p><br />\r\n<p>Assuring that employees are served with the unbiased reward system abreast with the fair distribution would encourage them to obtain more rewards simultaneously would generate more productivity. Also, it must be taken into consideration that engaging in cutting corners or favoritism will render a detrimental impact on the performance of the employees. Whereas, linking rewards to the performance would influence employees leaving a positive impact. Owing to such practices, the employees would be able to see the complete transparency in the work culture, organizational environment and would also apprehend the connection amid their rewards and performance. Thus, all of them will be automatically get motivated to optimally perform in the near future. </p><br />\r\n<p>In accordance with the met expected milestones, employees must be rewarded ensuring that they have fairly received the recognition for their progress including the consistency in their behavior as per the company’s expectations. In such a case, it’s better to discover the team based incentives because this could be effective enough to make employees passionate and enthusiast towards the work simultaneously would lead in increasing both the performance and productivity. However, if an organization doesn’t work on team-based rewards then, it must include it in its rewards program where devoted resources to team-based rewards must be substantial. Such a practice would surely go to leave a significant impact on employee’s cohesiveness as well as cooperation.<br/> <br />\r\nOn the contrary, there could also be a fatal flaw of not rewarding the top performers thusly, a good performer should never be taken for granted in order to maintain and flourish the top talent not only in the team but also in the organization. So, timely acknowledgment of rewards on excellent performance is a must. </p><br />\r\n<p>However, there is also some certain factor associated with maintenance of top talents which becomes obvious and natural after some point in time. This gets showcased when an employee makes it his behavioral habit. Hence, the managers should not offer the non-monetary rewards and recognition despite financial rewards which must be distributed depending on the variable ratio. </p><br />\r\n<p>It all depends on how well employees perform and at what extent does he dedicate himself. This could believe that long-term reward programs leave a positive effect on the overall performance leading to generate the long-lasting results. Whereas, frequent changes in the rewards also give employees surprise where process sometimes becomes excited as well. This excitement generates chaos amid the employees encouraging them to work hard and achieve more not individually but as a TEAM (together everyone achieves more). </p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,5000,2,'2020-01-13 10:12:48','2020-01-14 10:47:41'),(81,'5e1d4e3450cae',2,21,'Is Adultery a Crime or has been seriously Decriminalised by Supreme Court?','Adultery is a Crime or has been seriously Decriminalised by Supreme Court agreed in to social media','relationthinkstockphotos.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbt','<strong>Is Adultery a Crime or has been seriously Decriminalised by Supreme Court? </strong><br />\r\n<p> As per the declaration by <b>Supreme Court of India</b>, Adultery is not considered as a crime instead, has been declared as decriminalised by it. Having said that, the declaration of such law is unconstitutional as well as discriminatory against women. As per the judgement, a five-judge bench of the Supreme Court without opposition rule stated that having a sexual relationship with a female without her husband’s knowledge was a criminal offence. On the contrary, as stated above, it has been unconstitutional and has not been accepted by the people to an extent. </p><br />\r\n<p><b>Section 497 of the Indian penal code states that adultery law must be gender-neutral as it could become an obstacle against a spouse abandoning their respective families.</b> This concern majorly applies to the rural areas where most of the families still live in the oldest tradition and have stereotype mindsets. Also, it majorly and obviously affects the strata of woman that wield a little power especially when it comes to the patriarchal areas of some districts in the country.<br/><br />\r\nWith an alarming concern of the rising adultery in the nation, most of the women also approach to the respective commissions or other governmental bodies stating that their husband act in an adulterous manner, behave weirdly and have left them to take care and look after their children. Therefore, a heavy amount of the woman can get justice with the law wherein, their husband feels themselves in a kind of fear whilst entering into a new relationship. Also, they feel it like sanctity via which, they have to live with. </p><br />\r\n<p>On the other hand, the Delhi high court is also examining some other laws at the current moments making an exception for sexual assault. However, it would be applied only if both the victims as well as the perpetrator are married. Henceforth, most of the different men’s right group including the ruling government and other associated bodies have filed a petition against the marriage exception scrapping.</p><br />\r\n<p>So, while wrapping up, again, some of the above-mentioned concerns are highly required to be enlightened and must be taken into consideration. Additionally, while such kind of judgement is found to have a fearing impact amid the people, could impact a large number of marriages in India. Therein, the fallouts also couldn’t be overlooked or ignored. <br/><br />\r\nIn India, with the rising rates of the divorce, marital infidelity and varied forms of the associated cases with it can seriously endanger the institution of marriage. In fact, such cases can not only foster the risk of extra-marital affairs instead, the emergence of divorce would also catalyze breaking-up the vows of holy marriages. </p><br />\r\n<p>And, the worst part is that it\'s only the children who have to suffer at last just because of the misunderstanding, disputes and separation of their parents. <br/><br />\r\nAlso, under the adultery law, it is also stated that it\'s only the spouse of a married woman who had a right of filing a case against the man with whom she commits adultery and other physical relationships. But, <b>after the commitments and judgements provided by the Supreme Court</b>, such law won’t prevail. </p><br />\r\n<p>Alongside this, as per the section 497 of Indian Penal Code, Supreme Court has struck section 198 of Code of Criminal Procedure allowing the spouse to bring the charges against a man committing adultery with his respective wife. <br/><br />\r\nUndoubtedly, with such serious concerns, the marriages could surely have a break down wherein; the future of the children could be in a lurch. Therefore, the prominent concerns for both the married man and woman are to file a divorce if they find their partner committing adultery with someone else.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,5000,2,'2020-01-14 05:14:28','2020-01-14 10:47:45'),(82,'5e255827adf48',3,503,'Does Family Planning Restrict to Mutual Decisions or Forceful Obligation?','Family Planning Restrict on social media','couple-with-kid.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbu','<strong>Does Family Planning Restrict to Mutual Decisions or Forceful Obligation?</strong><br />\r\n<p>Family Planning – Do we really think to have a baby? In other words, a baby is born with proper planning or just gets an accidental birth. This article would tell the real meaning, importance, benefits, advantages and almost everything associated with family planning.</p><br />\r\n<p>Before going in detail, just enlighten the history and some facts and findings of family planning as stated and quoted by the International Conference on Human Rights since 1968.</p><br />\r\n<p> In accordance with the conference, family planning is globally affirmed human right which is not limited to a married couple but applies to the entire members of a family, irrespective of the gender. As per the document released by the conference which is also called Teheran Proclamation, it clearly states that <b>“Parents have a basic human right to determine freely and responsibly the number and spacing of their children.”</b></p><br />\r\n<p>On the other hand, it is also important to note that, India being the vast population country, one can’t overlook the implications of population explosion. Therein, over the last couple of years, the population growth is found on the urge to exceed more and more, by and far. Additionally, it is also notable that this urge of the population has reached to the surge due to the contributions of socio-economic culture and conditions, historical facts, policy changes and a lot more. </p><br />\r\n<p>Thus, people of the country are requested to deliver a limited as well as a planned baby which would help in the contribution of the quality population whilst population growth and control. </p><br />\r\n<p> Therefore, for a purpose of upholding a right quality family planning, people should concentrate on the below-mentioned parameters that are required to be implemented, monitored and regulated for the healthy changes in the concerning family planning.</p><br />\r\n<strong>No Gender Biasness</strong><br />\r\n<p> Family Planning including all the concerns associated with it must not be restricted to any sex, caste, creed, race, gender, religions, political views, language, nationality, economic status, native place, marital status, disability status etc. Doing so could result in ‘n’ numbers of mental trauma inside the person expecting to have a newborn. </p><br />\r\n<strong> Awareness</strong><br />\r\n<p> Coming to the precautions and contraceptive pills, proper information, awareness and knowledge must be circulated to everyone without hesitations. Sex education is necessary especially when it comes to serious concerns like Family Planning. Thus, sex education should be available to everyone at the right age and time based on the fractioning needs, differentiating factors and some little barriers associated with the same. Hence, it becomes exceptionally essential to understand the information’s quality depending on the background, education and health infrastructure. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Hassle-Free Implementation of Ideologies for Family Planning </strong><br />\r\n<p>When it comes to the implementation and formulation of the entire guidelines in the context of the <b>family planning</b>, there must not be a lack of access towards the hassle-free implementation. Here, access means the level and depth of rigor pertaining to accessibility and affordability. Herein, both the physical accessibility as well as affordability is the two major components that must be taken into consideration while thinking of expanding your generation or family. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Healthy Acceptance of Contraceptives </strong><br />\r\n<p>While intimacy and <strong>another discussion of family planning</strong>, it is highly suggestible to properly make use of contraceptive products that too in a dignified way while respecting the modern ways of medical policies and ethics as well. </p><br />\r\n<strong>No hide and seek in communication</strong><br />\r\n<p> While having a discussion about other members of the family pertaining to the concerns and issues of family planning, proper communication with respect to everyone’s acceptance and ideologies must be respected. This is so because; a small idea or view of any family member could guide a spouse towards the right ways. Thus, clear communication is necessary without pressurizing and provoking anyone. Moreover, coming to the contraceptive commodities, it must be purchased and rendered by sophisticated sanitary personnel. </p><br />\r\n<strong> Informed & Mutual Decisions </strong><br />\r\n<p> A family doesn’t restrict to the spouse and parents instead while panning a baby, most of the relations start getting connected with each other and with a baby as well before his or her birth in the world. So, while thinking of the <b>family planning</b>, each member of the family must be informed well enough reflecting free misrepresentation of the views and personal relationship. Herein, contraceptive counseling essentially becomes comprehensive equipping members to apprehend their decisions.</p><br />\r\n<strong> Not Disclosing the Maternity Matters </strong><br />\r\n<p>Best and healthy treatment is the most crucial factor to attain during family planning and other further processes of the same. Therefore, maintaining complete confidentiality, privacy and security in the treatment and other decisions must be locked amid the doctors, health workers, co-staff and other members as well. This is so because, there are a lot of people who visit the maternity centers every day, disclosing the patient’s history would affect all in making effective decisions for planning a baby. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Women Involvement with no Forceful Decisions </strong><br />\r\n<p>While planning a family to conceive and deliver a baby, at last, it’s the woman only who has to deliver a baby. Thus, this must be ensured that the woman who becomes the recipient for family planning should be well prepared when it comes to the development spheres influencing her decision and other health measures. Additionally, when it comes to the policies concerning reproductive and sexual health, family planning must be called from an educational and healthy point of views involving gynecologists, doctors, and other co-working staff members.<br/><br />\r\nImperative accountability must be reflected in the massive family members majorly by doctors, sex educators, and lifestyle specialists, health personnel majorly including family doctors, physicians and gynecologists etc. in order to maintain a high standard of accountability. Owing to this, whatever efforts they would be putting would definitely bring the fruitful results in marginalizing people while making them self aware and informed simultaneously empowering them to make informed and positive decisions. <br/><br />\r\nFollowing all such essential parameters would help in implementing a healthy and quality <b>family planning irrespective </b>of any differences. Also, World Population Day has assisted every one of us <b>spreading positive efforts about the holistic awareness of sex education while making healthy and informed decisions with best practices.</b> </p><br />\r\n <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,5000,2,'2020-01-20 07:35:03','2020-01-21 17:08:54'),(83,'5e2eaf0e0f6bc',1,502,'Increasing Robbery, Growing Theft Should Result Accused in a Major Suspect','Increasing Robbery, Growing Theft Should Result Accused in a Major Suspect on social media','robbery.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbv','<strong>Increasing Robbery, Growing Theft Should Result Accused in a Major Suspect</strong> <br />\r\n<p>Since the past few years in India, Robbery and other associated criminal rates are increasing at a massive pace. Ranging from chain snatching to mobile, cash, electronic gadgets and a lot more gets robbed or snatched away by various unexpected and surprising threatening tricks in just a blink of an eye. Herein, the practice of hypnotism is also encouraging robbers to take away the people’s belongings by their own will and wish.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Cases over Case, Reports are noted but gets Unnoticed </strong><br />\r\n<p>Over the past few years, Indians are being in a tap of such crime that people are not safe in their own house ranging from dusk and dawn. This is so because; there is no fixed time of robbers to attack and to rob. Therein, many shocking cases are being increasingly growing majorly in India. Every year, there have been a dozen reports that get noted in the police station for investigation and verification but unfortunately, nothing gets into consideration. Owing to such unethical practices of both the police and robbers, robberies of varied different belongings have become a business amongst illiterate and uneducated youth.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Robbery begins from one\'s own self </strong><br />\r\n<p>Moreover, youngsters are heavy in number, majorly of the teenage and the people up to an age of 25 years old. It’s completely an obvious fact that such people are more prone to drug addiction, drinking, smoking, adultery etc. and once they get addicted or attracted towards it, their only source of buying their stuff becomes either robbery or stealing. The unacceptable but the real fact is that it begins from one\'s own house itself such as taking away money from parents wallet without even informing them. This stealing of smaller amount later leads to the major robberies outside from their home. </p><br />\r\n<p>Such unethical, as well as illegal practices, have now become unsafe for the people to normally walk on the streets and roads majorly in the context of females. On the isolated streets, bikers come in a pair with the very fast speed and snatch away the gold or other materialistic belongings, mobile phones, cash, wallets etc whilst showing a gun or knife. The worst part of their trick is that sometimes they show the artificial or toy gun which seems like an original sample just to threat the people hovering around. Additionally, such incidents sound to happen in the deserted streets but unfortunately, it happens in the crowded areas where just because of the threatening practices people become helpless to help each other and other records the videos of the incident. </p><br />\r\n<p>Several times, any such sudden and threatening incidents leave the victim in a brutal state of mind, scared and injured that draws the attention of the general public present at the incident’s spot wherein, any one of them who feels essential to inform police, inform them, rest other just remain same in their happening activities.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Also, these robbers are so cunning and smart that while performing robbery or snatching something, they change their clothes that increase their chances of not being caught. Most often these robbers either carry a pair of extra jacket or shirt with them and always apply some lubricated substances on their body so that, if they get cached by someone they could easily slip and can run away. After acquiring the stolen goods, these robbers sell the desired products and earn their desirable profits. </p><br />\r\n<p>Their smooth escaping practice makes them difficult to trace whereas, surveillance of CCTV sometimes could help to an extent. Owing to this, police have now become familiar with their unethical practices but unfortunately, do nothing until and unless they seem their own profit in helping the victim by any means or by a bribe. </p> <br />\r\n<strong>If such remains continue to happen then, where would our nation go? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Thus, people are requested especially the females to carry the essential precautionary measures with them such as a pepper spray, a pointed pen, knife or anything that could be beneficial in self-defense.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Eat, Repeat and Sleep – Robbery </strong><br />\r\n<p>Moreover, if an accused get caught and punished, their punishment gets restricted till imprisonment of some time. After getting released, they do the same practices again just to eat, repeat and sleep which happens in the jail as well. So, such people don’t get affected while getting caught. </p><br />\r\n<p>Thus, this won’t work in building a better as well as the developed nation instead; both the purpose and practice of crime highly need to be figured out. If this could be done, the prisoners must be rehabilitated prior to getting bailed or released. Also, they should be gone to some psychiatric therapy sessions so that no individual gets threatened again and feel unsafe on hovering on the isolated streets. <br/> <br />\r\nHence, by identifying the root cause of the problem and solving it accordingly could work better with time, somehow and someday.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,5000,2,'2020-01-27 15:06:14','2020-02-07 18:14:46'),(84,'5e32ba8e9b63d',2,505,'Does the server you use, protects your business or leads it towards Cyber Crime – DDoS ','Does the server you use, protects your business or leads it towards Cyber Crime – Odds  using ','anti-attacks.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbw','<strong>Does the server you use, protects your business or leads it towards Cyber Crime – DDoS Servers</strong><br />\r\n<p>It is natural that risk of cyber-attack is associated with each step taken by the world into the era of the digital age. Owing to this, such a risk has also become a bit daunting threat as well. Thus, with the rising risk of the cyber-attacks, (DDoS Protected Dedicated Servers) are receiving superior attention in the past few years abreast with a good reason of existence. Therefore, a DDoS attack is just an attempt in making unavailability of online service by overwhelming it via traffic from multiple sources.</p><br />\r\n<strong> DDoS Protected Dedicated Servers are so concerning? </strong><br />\r\n<p>The fundamental answer to reflecting such a concern is that such servers are relatively easy to implement. So, with the help of such servers, botnets could be easily purchased from the black market for better use of DDoS. </p><br />\r\n<p>Potential outcomes from DDoS attacks are listed below: </p><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<li>•    Operational Activities Interruption </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Financial impacts because of revenue, productivity and data loss </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Funding decreased ability and reputation damage </li><br />\r\n</ul><br />\r\n<p>Alongside this, there are a large number of the additional fraud activities as well for which most of the cybercriminals make use of the DDoS to have access to the information which they really try to get on their hands. </p><br />\r\n<p>On the contrary, when it comes to the types of business, the attackers of DDoS never discriminate on it. It means that your business is not immune to such kind of activity. Therefore, there are a lot of industries that are receiving such kind of increasing attention with help DDoS attacks. Some of which are mentioned below: </p><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<li>•    Healthcare </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Hospitality </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Federal Government </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Local Government </li><br />\r\n<li>•    K-12 Education </li><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<strong>Alongside this, a question here arises that: <br><br />\r\nHow to Protect Your Business from DDoS Attack? </strong><br />\r\n<p>The attackers of DDoS can attack the occupation at any point in time. No matter what industry are you in? You just need to keep below-listed recommendations so as to protect your business from DDoS attacks<br />\r\nKnow your security concerns and create a defensive strategy:<br><br />\r\nIn order to assure that your business is completely safe and protected from DDoS attacks, you just need to develop the security policy of IT. One such security gets developed, be sure to share it with personnel of all the companies and assure that you have a secure network.<br> <br />\r\nUp-to-Date Security Safeguards: <br><br />\r\nTo defend your system from DDoS attack in all the best possible ways, it is mandatory that all your hardware, software, as well as other security safeguards, are up to date. Apart from this, strict password policies are often paramount and mandatory in keeping your systems secure. Thus, below-listed points would help you in developing all forms of business-related passwords such as: </p><br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n<li>•    Create a unique password for each account </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Create a password with a blend of letters, numbers, and symbols </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Never use common words and personal information </li><br />\r\n<li>•    Update and change your password on equal time intervals </li><br />\r\n</ul><br />\r\n<strong>Concentrate on Network Security</strong><br />\r\n<p>Concentrating on the concerns of your network security, it’s better to keep in a touch with a network security specialist who consists of the knowledge and years of experience with cybersecurity. This is because his assistance holding such of the specialities would be highly able to give compete for network security at times as per the needs of the people and end-users. <br/><br />\r\nSo, what if a DDoS Attack Happens to Your Business? What to do in such a case? <br/><br />\r\nPrepare yourself to know that defending your business from DDoS attacks will not stop with mitigation and prevention. Therefore, it is very mandatory for your business to include a response plan as a member of its defence strategy. Having such kind of plan would help you rebound faster from the attacks.<br/><br />\r\nIn addition to this, it is also suggested to work with your ISP to see if they offer DDoS protection services so that if an attack occurs in a near-future then, you may let them know and they may reroute the traffic from a site prior to substantial damage is done. </p><br />\r\n<p>So, always assure that, whenever DDoS attacks are found to be on the rise, all such steps must be taken into consideration in order to mitigate the associated risks of these attacks. Also, note that no one in the world is so immune towards the cyber-attack. So, it’s better to always be ready and prepare yourself accordingly for the damaging cyber-attack.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,3800,2,'2020-01-30 16:44:22','2020-02-07 18:14:33'),(85,'5e32bcc92f1de',2,505,'Does the server you use, protects your business or leads it towards Cyber Crime – DDoS Servers','Does the server you use, protects your business or leads it towards Cyber Crime – DDoS Servers on social media','anti-attacks.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbx','<strong>Does the server you use, protects your business or leads it towards Cyber Crime – DDoS Servers</strong><br />\r\n<p>It is natural that risk of cyber-attack is associated with each step taken by the world into the era of the digital age. Owing to this, such a risk has also become a bit daunting threat as well. Thus, with the rising risk of the cyber-attacks, (DDoS Protected Dedicated Servers) are receiving superior attention in the past few years abreast with a good reason of existence. Therefore, a DDoS attack is just an attempt in making unavailability of online service by overwhelming it via traffic from multiple sources.</p><br />\r\n<strong> DDoS Protected Dedicated Servers are so concerning? </strong><br />\r\n<p>The fundamental answer to reflecting such a concern is that such servers are relatively easy to implement. So, with the help of such servers, botnets could be easily purchased from the black market for better use of DDoS. </p><br />\r\n<p>Potential outcomes from DDoS attacks are listed below: </p><br />\r\n•    Operational Activities Interruption <br/><br />\r\n•    Financial impacts because of revenue, productivity and data loss <br/><br />\r\n•    Funding decreased ability and reputation damage <br/><br />\r\n<p>Alongside this, there are a large number of the additional fraud activities as well for which most of the cybercriminals make use of the DDoS to have access to the information which they really try to get on their hands. </p><br />\r\n<p>On the contrary, when it comes to the types of business, the attackers of DDoS never discriminate on it. It means that your business is not immune to such kind of activity. Therefore, there are a lot of industries that are receiving such kind of increasing attention with help DDoS attacks. Some of which are mentioned below: </p><br />\r\n•    Healthcare <br/><br />\r\n•    Hospitality <br/><br />\r\n•    Federal Government <br/><br />\r\n•    Local Government <br/><br />\r\n•    K-12 Education <br/><br />\r\n<strong>Alongside this, a question here arises that: <br/><br />\r\nHow to Protect Your Business from DDoS Attack? </strong><br />\r\n<p>The attackers of DDoS can attack the occupation at any point in time. No matter what industry are you in? You just need to keep below-listed recommendations so as to protect your business from DDoS attacks<br />\r\nKnow your security concerns and create a defensive strategy:<br/><br />\r\nIn order to assure that your business is completely safe and protected from DDoS attacks, you just need to develop the security policy of IT. One such security gets developed, be sure to share it with personnel of all the companies and assure that you have a secure network.<br/> <br />\r\nUp-to-Date Security Safeguards: <br/><br />\r\nTo defend your system from DDoS attack in all the best possible ways, it is mandatory that all your hardware, software, as well as other security safeguards, are up to date. Apart from this, strict password policies are often paramount and mandatory in keeping your systems secure. Thus, below-listed points would help you in developing all forms of business-related passwords such as: </p><br />\r\n•    Create a unique password for each account <br/><br />\r\n•    Create a password with a blend of letters, numbers, and symbols <br/><br />\r\n•    Never use common words and personal information <br/><br />\r\n•    Update and change your password on equal time intervals <br/><br />\r\n<strong>Concentrate on Network Security</strong><br />\r\n<p>Concentrating on the concerns of your network security, it’s better to keep in a touch with a network security specialist who consists of the knowledge and years of experience with cybersecurity. This is because his assistance holding such of the specialities would be highly able to give compete for network security at times as per the needs of the people and end-users. <br/><br />\r\nSo, what if a DDoS Attack Happens to Your Business? What to do in such a case? <br/><br />\r\nPrepare yourself to know that defending your business from DDoS attacks will not stop with mitigation and prevention. Therefore, it is very mandatory for your business to include a response plan as a member of its defence strategy. Having such kind of plan would help you rebound faster from the attacks.<br/><br />\r\nIn addition to this, it is also suggested to work with your ISP to see if they offer DDoS protection services so that if an attack occurs in a near-future then, you may let them know and they may reroute the traffic from a site prior to substantial damage is done. </p><br />\r\n<p>So, always assure that, whenever DDoS attacks are found to be on the rise, all such steps must be taken into consideration in order to mitigate the associated risks of these attacks. Also, note that no one in the world is so immune towards the cyber-attack. So, it’s better to always be ready and prepare yourself accordingly for the damaging cyber-attack.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,4500,2,'2020-01-30 16:53:53','2020-02-07 18:14:30'),(86,'5e32c111e945f',2,505,'Internet & Internet of Things (IoT) a boon or bane for the Users','Internet & Internet of Things','Cybercrime.png','https://callupon.org/stby','<strong>Internet & Internet of Things (IoT) a boon or bane for the Users</strong><br />\r\n<b>Indeed, omnipresent is the world of Cyber…</b><br />\r\n<p>How surprising is that our morning begins with internet and ends with the same. Instead, it’s not only the social media that allure us to Facebook, WhatsApp or other social platforms as the new ways of saying Good Morning but there are numerous ways of getting both affected and effected with the same.<br />\r\nTalking about the new age technologies especially the Internet of Things (IoT), it has transformed each small era of everyone’s life. Ranging from toys which have been also turned into digitized way via remote controls, self-driving cars with AI and there are ‘n’ number of things that surrounds us daily. Undoubtedly, every electronic gadget or other associated appliances have computing and could be connected with the internet. This doesn’t get restricted only till desktop and laptop but majorly it’s the mobile devices that act as a major weapon towards cybercrimes.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Cyber Security in Digitized Banking </strong><br />\r\n<p>Even if today, a person’s sentiment might swerve towards avoiding technology but there are some government policies and procedures as well that strive their best in making India a digital as well as the smart country. This not only uses the technology but has also enabled the people with essential and reasonable security too. Owing to the branding, promotion and marketing of cashless India, technology and internet have positively encouraged the people in their everyday life.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Cyber Crime as a Threat via Social Networking </strong> <br />\r\n<p>Alongside the system of digitized banking, the major alarming concern is social networking sites that must be a major trap under cyber laws. Majorly if it is focussed on relationships that have been carried by social networking sites that have threatened people till a huge extent and have also resulted in the drastic and adverse effects. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Crimes are bound with Revenge’s Feeling </strong><br />\r\n<p>Crimes amongst people are bound with a feeling of revenge especially when a couple breaks up. Herein, MMS and porn have become the popular strategy to mentally torture anyone. Due to this, people upload personal pictures and videos majorly nudes or semi nudes and blackmail the concerned person whose content has been uploaded.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Life is taken for granted</strong> <br />\r\n<p>Additionally, most of the cases of morphing faces have also ruined the victim’s life leading to death or another form of losses in life. The doer of the crimes takes it as a granted and feels some delight out of its outcomes but doesn’t even realize the trauma that a victim suffers from. Such crimes do not cost a single penny but result in the major loss of life. However, the only encouraging common ground for such crimes is the mobile and internet connection.<br/><br />\r\nThese crimes do not cost anything with mobile phones and internet connections being commonplace wherein, both child pornography, as well as pornography, closes the circuit of heinous online crimes.<br/><br />\r\nSo, what to do?<br/><br />\r\nWith such the rising rates, of the life losing and threat causing concerns, sitting like a sitter won’t work. The actions taken only by the government by banning such sites or other associated parameters are not enough. One needs to take his or her own stand being stronger at each suffering phase. Though its true and undenied fact that internet has leveraged all our lives to a much higher extent simultaneously, this fact also could not be denied that there are major drawbacks, threats, losses and causes associated with the same.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,5000,2,'2020-01-30 17:12:09','2020-02-07 18:14:26'),(87,'5e393d26d4887',2,21,'Censor Free Content on the Internet is proven to be Engaging or Diverging Audience','Censor Free Content on the Internet is proven to be Engaging or Diverging Audience spread on social media','China-network.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbz','<strong>Censor Free Content on the Internet is proven to be Engaging or Diverging Audience </strong><br />\r\n<p>In the present scenario, today is the time of technology and advancements in almost all varied entertaining modes and industries. Time has flown when people were supposed to sit in front of a TV on Sundays and were fully dependent on DDs Channel. This 21st century fledges with technical advancements affecting all the aspects of human life. So, if we speak about the (digital TV), probably, you can explore the world and its associated spice within a fraction of seconds.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Censor-Free Content - a fun BELOVED & LOVED by all </strong><br />\r\n<p>No doubt, it is correct saying that all of us require some spice and fun for entertainment where definitely, the path of entertainment and fun may seem variable. This is so because constancy always creates boredom to an extent. Several times, a person prefers different sorts of fun activities wherein, social media and availability of censor-free content on the Internet are preferred the most. Talking about the easy availability of censor-free content, these days, films are being released at no cost on different internet platforms such as Netflix, Alt Balaji, Zee 5 and there are ‘n’ number of such platforms. </p><br />\r\n<p>It has proven both as the boon and bane for the Indian society affecting the socio-cultural implications of the same as well. In today’s era of digitization where theatres and televisions are also turning to be digital, the early aspect for searching the content begins with such online platforms. It has not only influenced the social-cultural ethics of human life instead has also equally impacted life economic life of the people affecting their lifestyle, standard of living, ways of making expenses, gender, language, ethnicity and much more. </p><br />\r\n<strong>A biggest Hit to Online Platforms </strong><br />\r\n<p>Unfortunately or undoubtedly, such availability of censor-free content on internet platform has become a structure of dominance in cultural values affecting morals and encouraging adultery and crimes amid the people. On the other hand, the reflection of such content has also led the society towards innovation and smartness to cope up with the daily happenings and incidents of the society that has also proven to leave the society with the huge impacts. </p><br />\r\n<p>Today’s teenage and younger generation watches a broader spectrum of the romantic, lusty, controversial plots that encourage them to try it practically in their real-life. Such aspects majorly focus on homosexuality, transgender, child labor, poverty, unemployment, prostitution and a lot more till a huge extent. Such topics have brought a world together and united but have also departed people with each other. Where relationships were priorities, people especially vacant their time to meet and see each other has now been replaced by the online platform availing easy accessibility of censor-free content.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Everyone knows NOSTALGIA!!! </strong><br />\r\n<p>However, like a coin have two faces: the heads and the tails similarly, the presence of censor-free content has two factors; the advantages and the drawbacks. Neither all the content provokes people to commit any crime nor encourages the adultery amongst them meanwhile at the same time, it insists or attracts people towards the same and makes them an addict.</p><br />\r\n<p>Nowadays, the recent ongoing trends in the theatres & Bollywood are the daily introduction of new faces in the industry and releases of new movies on frequent time intervals. The same happens with the free availability of content on the Internet. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Contradiction...</strong><br />\r\n<p>It is not said that the movie is the only best option to entertain ones or yourself. Instead, there are varied other forms of the options as well as superior modes of entertainment via which you can laugh, enjoy, entertain and pamper yourself. It seems a little contradictory, but the fact is that... real entertainment is the only one via which you get self-satisfaction and pleasure. It can be anything, any activity etc.<br/><br />\r\nThe concept of censor-free content is deeper in itself which also constitutes major importance. An absence of the same would lead your life towards boredom and dullness. </p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,6500,2,'2020-02-04 15:15:10','2020-02-07 18:14:22'),(88,'5e3a5a185336f',1,503,'Corona Virus: An Epidemic, Spreading Globally Tapping People at Large Scale','Very Big issue  of Corona Virus An Epidemic, Spreading Globally Tapping People at Large Scale','Coronavirus.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbA','<strong>Corona Virus: An Epidemic, Spreading Globally Tapping People at Large Scale </strong><br />\r\n<p>When a person deals with <b>an epidemic</b>, he barely holds hope. This is actually so because the word epidemic itself comprises of a huge meaning in its existence. An epidemic could be anything which begins with a small symptom and later turns into a big disease and hence is termed <b>as Epidemic</b>.</p> <br />\r\n<p>These days, the same is happening in the case of Coronavirus. However, people are getting various information and facts regarding the virus and hence, is listed as the infodemic.<br/> <br />\r\nAs the Coronovirus is rapidly increasing in the major countries of the world wherein, China has been hugely tapped by it. The virus has been s threatening and has proven to be life taking amid the people that everyone fears with its name. The major issue is the recognition of the same i.e. how to analyse and diagnose that whether a person is suffering from some illness is either Coronavirus or something else. So, the symptoms and diagnosis of the virus are mentioned below: <br/><br />\r\n· Fever <br/><br />\r\n· Cough <br/><br />\r\n· Shortness of breath  <br/><br />\r\n· Runny Nose <br/><br />\r\n· Headache  <br/><br />\r\n· Sore Throat <br/><br />\r\nThough such symptoms are found to be very common and can be easily cured but in case of such virus, these symptoms should not be overlooked as it has caused a large number of deaths these days in just the couple of days. Thus, for confirmed, 2019-nCoV infections have reported a severe illness leading death. </p><br />\r\n<p>It is also believed that the symptoms of 2019-nCoV may appear either in 2 days or as long as in 14 days. Also, it is entirely based on the incubation period of the MERS virus. Apart from such noticeable symptoms, it also includes some other symptoms as well such as 229E, NL63, OC43, and HKU1. All such symptoms generally caused some upper-respiratory tract illnesses majorly in the context of common cold, pneumonia or bronchitis. However, such illness is basically found in the people suffering from cardiopulmonary disease and the people with the weaker immune system. </p><br />\r\n<p> In addition to this, one should also enlighten that the other two associated symptoms of Coronavirus i.e. MERS-CoV and SARS-CoV have also become frequently familiar with the people resulting in life-ending happenings. With the sufferings of such virus, approx. 3-4 people out of 10 have been sentenced to death on almost frequent hourly intervals. </p><br />\r\n<strong>What precautions one should take for avoidance and prevention of Coronavirus? </strong><br />\r\n•    Frequent hand washing with alcohol-based hand wash or liquid soap as it would help in killing the germs and virus. <br/><br />\r\n•    Maintain respiratory hygiene. This would be only performed while covering both face and mouth with tissue paper or handkerchief mainly while coughing and sneezing. Doing so would help in preventing the germs and virus and could contaminate the objects or people you come into contact with. <br/><br />\r\n•    Stop touching your mouth, face, nose and eyes because touching such surfaces could result in virus contamination. Touching such parts may result in virus transferring immensely and exceptionally. <br/><br />\r\n•    Avoid consuming animal’s products (all forms of non-veg) and stop being into contact with the animals like camel, rats, cats, rodents, birds, bats and dogs as well. <br/><br />\r\n<p>Therefore, the diagnosis of such symptoms has been essentially required to save people from the massively growing epidemic all around the clock. Your doctors and other health care providers should examine you by performing some of the laboratory tests on respiratory specimens all the major blood test (called serum) in order to detect the presence of Coronavirus if any. If you found the test with positive results, then, you must immediately contact your doctor informing him about your recent travelling, non-veg intake and animal’s contact. A large number of MERS-CoV infections has been detected from Arabian Peninsula’s country and so, it becomes highly essential to note and report about your travel diaries and history or animal’s contact. Herein, animal contact fundamentally means with contact with camel or camel diaries and products.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Thus, if you are suffering from fever, cough and cold then, you should immediately pay <br />\r\nattention to the same before it becomes serious or life-taking. </p>',0,0,0,10000,2,'2020-02-05 11:30:56','2020-02-07 18:14:16'),(89,'5e40d9fb17ebc',2,505,'Caste a Vote Because it’s a Right to Note: Country to Native Citizens','Caste a Vote Because it’s a Right to Note: Country to Native Citizens one vote one value is human rights','GettyImages.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbB','<strong>Caste a Vote Because it’s a Right to Note: Country to Native Citizens </strong><br />\r\n<b>One Vote, One Value…</b><br />\r\n<p> India being a democratic country gives its citizens complete liberty to choose the right ruler and representative for their country with no forces and influences. Lucky are the citizens of the country that gets served with such opportunities, timely. Whereas, commonly, it’s a well-known and genuine process of choosing a representative of their choice via Elections. </p><br />\r\n<p>A country which is democratic and values the people’s identity and dignity irrespective of any religion, caste or creed; faces and respects the process of Elections. Ranging from the election of Lok Sabha (General Election), State Assembly (Vidhan Sabha Election), By-election, Rajya Sabha (Upper House Election) each citizen of the nation has a complete right to vote. <br />\r\nAs mentioned above <strong>“One Vote, One Value”</strong> has a major meaning in itself that couldn’t be taken for granted. This majorly means that each candidate can vote once during the time of Elections to their preferred party. This is so because each casted vote gets counted to announce the results. It’s our casted vote that we perform to choose the party to be ruled after the results get announced on the specified date.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Sooner, the National Capital Region i.e. New Delhi is going to have Elections to choose the Chief Minister of the Nation. As of now, the present C.M. of Delhi is Mr Arvind Kejriwal who belongs to Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) having a symbol of Broom. Fingers Crossed, it all depends on the number of votes that whether again AAP is going to rule, or some other party would overtake AAP.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Polling Dates</strong><br />\r\n<p>Since the date of Election in Delhi has been announced as 8th February 2020 (Saturday), the Election Commission of India announced its complete schedule prior a month back in order to elect the legislative assembly of Delhi. Alongside this, the result will be announced on 11th February 2020 (Tuesday). </p><br />\r\n<p>In addition to this, as per the Election Commission of India, the vote’s counting would begin from early morning 8 am onwards until 6 pm on Saturday: 11th Feb. Whereas, the entire tenure of the present Delhi Legislative Assembly would come to an end on 22nd February 2020 (Saturday).</p>  <br />\r\n<strong>Political Parties are on Race</strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, all the casting voters must also enlighten that the Assembly Election 2020 would occur in a single phase abreast with the voting in all 70 constituencies which have been scheduled for Feb 8. All the political parties are cheering up and boosting themselves to be healthy as well as a successful part of the election. However, as per the political scenarios, there have been 3 concerned contests amid Congress, Bhartiya Janata Party (BJP) and Aam Aadmi Party (AAP). People just could only assume or predict based on their interest and votes that which party would going to rule. However, the final result will be declared on Feb 11. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Vote has a deeper meaning and value </strong><br />\r\n<p>So, cast your vote because your one vote can change the entire scenario, in fact, at the last moment and could lead a nation towards the healthy and developed ones. Thus, on the polling date i.e. on Feb 8, voters can exercise their franchise from morning 8 am onwards. However, it is also suggested, and one should make a note of it that, you should not vote to the candidate getting influenced by your near and dear ones. This is so because, most of the times, people vote to those parties by getting influenced from their friends, family members, relatives or other acquaintances. On the other hand, the people who influence others are also requested not to brainwash or influence others in such a way that their vote seems useless or gets wasted. Doing so results in malpractices for both the people; the one who gets influenced and the one who influences others. </p><br />\r\n<p>Observing all such observations, the Election Commission of India has moved towards the EVMs (Electronic Voting Machine). EVMs have replaced the concept of Ballot Papers because people were encouraging others for forceful voting and were encouraging the candidates towards the victory. Thus, such practices are of no use, if each one would influence others for forceful voting. Basically, such kind of practice had also become a monotony as well wherein, family traditions could be listed on top. This is so because, most of the Family’s HOD say that, we have always been a supporter of this particular party from our generations so, we will be casting our vote to the same without knowing that what are their right and wrongdoings.<br />\r\nSo, open up your mind and be so rational to caste a right vote to the right candidate or a ruling party.  </p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,6000,1,'2020-02-10 09:50:11','2020-02-10 09:50:11'),(90,'5e40f2a842441',2,502,'Why Justice gets Delay and the Process Remains in Dates over Dates?','Why Justice gets Delay and the Process Remains in Dates over Dates on social media','main-qimg.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbC','<strong>Why Justice gets Delay and the Process Remains in Dates over Dates? </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Yes!!! You heard right.</strong><br />\r\n<p> Why a girl who got raped on December 16, 2012, is not getting justice since then which should be announced to her criminals instantly during the incident.<br />\r\nRape is not a mistake but is a crime. The raped girl named “Nirbhaya” died because of her brutal and severe injuries in a Singapore hospital but unfortunately, her culprits are still alive till date. Wherein, it was expected that her culprits were expected to be hanged on January 22, 2020, in Delhi’s Tihar Jail, it got postponed for February 1st in the early morning at 6 am and now is continuously getting delay and dates over dates.</p><br />\r\n<p>This unethical behavior of delaying justice is disturbing the nation and most specifically the accused mother. Nirbhaya’s mom is eagerly waiting for the culprit’s punishment. Every time she stands with a hope of some good news for the culprits to be hung but unfortunately and alas!!! Instead of getting punishment, the tenure of their life is getting extended while delaying justice.</p><br />\r\n<p>Nirbhaya means fearless. Jyoti Singh who was 23 years old physiotherapist was gang-raped in a running bus at Munirka in South Delhi. She was so brutally raped, assaulted and thrown out of the bus with her friend (Avanindra Pandey). Because of this incident, Jyoti is named as Nirbhaya. Her friend was also assaulted. Both of them were thrown out of the moving bus wherein, the girl was thrown nude. Her boyfriend tried his best to save her life but unfortunately because of the severe internal injuries she was half dead and declared died in Singapore hospital. Doctor’s strived and tried their best to save her but just because of the lust of the 6 culprits, the girl exists no more. </p><br />\r\n<p>Out of the 6 people, 4 were the culprits wherein, Ram Singh and a juvenile were named as accused. However, the trial of the 5 adult men initiated in the special fast-track court since March 2013 but as of now, nation can see that since the beginning till date nothing has been changed instead, the culprits need of eating, sleep and repeat is getting extended. </p><br />\r\n<p>Ram Singh was the primary accused who allegedly committed a suicidal attempt in Tihar Jail by hanging himself after the beginning f the trial by the special fast track court. On the other hand, as per the concerns of the juvenile, who was also said to be the most brutal amongst all of the people, was sent to the Juvenile for 3 years.<br />\r\nAgreed if that Juvenile was eligible to be sent to the Juvenile for 3 years that absolutely doesn’t mean that his punishment was sufficient enough. Since the date of the incident, it has been almost 7-8 years, the juvenile would not remain juvenile. Additionally, the accused mainly named Mukesh Sharma, Vinay Sharma, Akshay Thakur, Pawan Gupta have been also grown and definitely could not be of the same age that they were during committing a crime. </p><br />\r\n<p>So, with such delays definitely, the aggression would rise in the nation’s peeps and especially in all the near and dear ones, those who are associated with Jyoti Singh. The nation needs a proper justice and answer to this heinous crime. What went wrong at that time and what is going wrong at present?</p><br />\r\n<p>As per the sources and news, it has been stated that the Supreme Court of India will hear the case on Tuesday wherein, the government of both the Central as well as the State Delhi has requested for a separate hanging for the 4 convicts. Most interestingly, the government had also challenged the verdict of Delhi High Court dismissing its plea against the execution of 4 men stay. This is because, the government had wanted a proper notice to be sent to 4 convicts wherein, a judicial bench headed by Justice R Bhanumathi hadn’t heeded this request and said that, the matter would delay further.</p><br />\r\n<p>Owing to this, the patience of the nations is being tested. Additionally, Vinay Sharma did file a mercy petition in front of President Ram Nath Kovind wherein, his appeal had turned down to another convict Akshay Singh filing a mercy plea. Filing mercy petitions have shown that the convicts are trying their level best to be released without being punished and are making each possible effort and loopholes to delay the execution.</p><br />\r\n<p>With seeing all such potential efforts of convicts, the Delhi High Court has given them a week time to finish exploring the legal help and thereafter the trial court will again start the proceedings for the execution of the case to come to an end. </p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,8000,1,'2020-02-10 11:35:28','2020-02-10 11:35:28'),(91,'5e42a00ca31e8',8,21,'Now the protests would rule the nation to make any decision or it has become a trend to get-the-point?','Now the protests would rule the nation to make any decision or it has become a trend to get-the-point on social media','xEcuador-Protest.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbD','<strong>Now the protests would rule the nation to make any decision or it has become a trend to get-the-point? </strong><br />\r\n<p>India is suffering from a constant protest of Shaheen Bagh is adversely affecting everyone i.e. both the participants of the protest and the general public as well which is not involved in it. This 24*7 ongoing protest has also termed as sit-in peaceful protest which formerly led by women with the passage of CAA since 11 December 2019. The initial purpose of the protest was to assure the cops intervention against Jamia’s students who were strongly opposing the amendment of citizenship act.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>What’s the use of doing the protest and creating violence? </strong><br />\r\n<p>It’s resulting in nothing except the threat to women’s safety, commodities rising cost, unemployment, poverty and a lot of more societal threats. With a major count of Muslim women, the constant protestors have also blocked various roads in Delhi NCR since December 15, 2019, using non-violent resistance for more than 55 days. Unfortunately, no one could say that how long these days are going to stretch. As of now, this protest has proven to be one of the longest on-going protests towards CAA, NRC & NPRA in India.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Reforming Phrase… </strong><br />\r\n<p>More or less, the protest is taking a new shape by and by as well as day by day. Since with its beginning with the citizenship amendment act, it has now started protesting against the BJP’s Government. Owing to this, the protestors are opposing the government\'s <strong>\"anti-labour policies\"</strong> and <strong>“2020 JNU Attack”</strong> as well.</p> <br />\r\n<strong>Petition over Petition… Highway’s Blockade </strong><br />\r\n<p>The issues of highway blocking also called (blockade) had also become a campaign for 2020 Delhi’s Legislative Assembly Election with a promise made by campaigners that if the party gets voted into power the blockade would be removed for the election’s day. Moreover, the blockade affected huge traffic in a day abreast with delays of hours in the shortest journeys. </p><br />\r\n<p>Owing to this, around 5 petitions have been filed, as of now raising the issue of highways and roads blockade wherein, the Delhi High Court refused the hearings of initial 2 pleas and quoted towards the police matter. Simultaneously, on the other hand, the Delhi Police stated that they would use persuasion over force to take blockade at an end. When, this also failed to bring the result, again a third petition was filed on 18th January 2020 raising the student’s difficulty specifically during the exam’s time. Therein, the High Court again appeal the police to investigate the matter. Unfortunately, the situation went out of control and the matter reached to the Supreme Court with filed pleas wherein, it has been expected that after the occasion of national importance (elections), the pleas would be enlightened. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Why disturbance in Nation? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Well, alongside all such concerns, issues, violence and riots, one must also thoroughly know the root cause of all such disrupting happenings inside the nation. The CAA (Citizenship Amendment Act) was passed by the Indian Parliament on 12th December 2019 that amends the Citizenship Act of 1995. Under the religious persecution’s assumptions, it granted a swifter way to Indian citizenship mainly to those people who belong to minorities like Hindu, Sikh, Buddhist, Jains, Parsi, Christians and people mainly from Afghanistan, Bangladesh and Pakistan. This act also meant for those people who entered India before 31st December 2014. Whereas, neither the act mentioned Muslims, nor did they offer the associated benefits to Muslim immigrants. Additionally, the worst part of the protest is that it has been immensely affecting the country’s economic crisis witnessing an increasing household debt as well as decreasing growth rate in income and other earning sources. </p><br />\r\n<strong>What’s Indifferent? </strong><br />\r\n<p>The protest of Shaheen Bagh began with a minimum of 10-15 women since 14th December 2019. Afterwards, this 2-digit number got extended to the strength of thousands and lakhs. Many people joined the protests including the students and children which then became 24*7 protest. Also, amid the huge crowd, most of the women were Muslim as they found of wearing a burqa. The unacceptable truth is that females with the new born babies or the lactating ones are also a part of this unworthy constant protest. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Hunger Strike</strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, to lead this protest further in most exceptional ways, many of the people amid the crowd have started volunteering it in different ways like Hunger Strike and Children Protest. Owing to this, few of the protestors were on hunger strike for days and later on got hospitalised. What was the use of doing this? Instead, one’s own health got affected and nothing happened, nothing got changed. The reason for the hunger strike was the police brutality on the students, violence on females in Jamia washroom’s and library and all the associated issues with the case. With the hunger strike, people also demanded the rollback of NRC and CAA. Unfortunately, no government office or associated governmental bodies took this hunger strike into consideration and even didn’t visit the protestors of the same. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Misinformation Misleading Children…Child Protest</strong><br />\r\n<p>Also, since day 1 of the strike, many of the children started joining their parents to participate in the strike. In the morning they attend their school afterwards they become the strike’s participant. Now, it seems like Shaheen Bagh has become an artistic space for most of the children because they express their thoughts through poetry, storytelling, mimicry, puppetry and painting graffiti. In fact, many children participate in the sit-in protest holding candles in their hands. Participating children in the protest get dressed in tricolour and express the informed thoughts by their parents.</p> <br />\r\n<p>Observing all such unethical practices, since 21st January 2020, the NCPCR (National Commission for Protection of Child Rights) has asked the concern authorities to guide the children providing the counselling towards the protests while making them understand what’s right and what’s wrong. This is so because such drastic concerns could also drive the children towards the mental trauma likewise the way they are undergoing with the provided misinformation. </p><br />\r\n<strong>The nation needs the right way to run where unity needs priorities over protests. </strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n ',0,0,0,7000,1,'2020-02-11 18:07:32','2020-02-11 18:07:32'),(92,'5e452081bf68d',3,502,'The Crucial Cursing Concern: Nipah Virus, A Hilarious Epidemic  <br/> Scientific Facts and Origin','The Crucial Cursing Concern: Nipah Virus, A Hilarious Epidemic  <br/> Scientific Facts and Origin safe the baby this virus','nipah-virus.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbE','<strong>The Crucial Cursing Concern: Nipah Virus, A Hilarious Epidemic  <br/><br />\r\nScientific Facts and Origin: </strong><br />\r\n<p>Nipah Virus is a sort of the viral zoonotic disease which is originated from NiV of the Henipavirus genus of Paramyxoviridae family. The virus is mainly getting a widespread because of the Pteropodidae Family, Pteropus genus bats (fruit-eating species specifically called as flying foxes) which are also supposed to be the virus\'s natural hosts. However, this severe emerging zoonosis is also responsible for causing the diseases in both human beings and animals. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Findings & Origin: </strong><br />\r\n•    However, it was first identified during the disease\'s outbreak which first took place in Kampung Sungai Nipah, Malaysia in 1998. At that time, the fundamental intermediate hosts were the pigs.<br/> <br />\r\n•    With the passage of time abreast with the subsequent NiV outbreaks, there were no intermediate hosts but still, people became infected resulted in an intake or consumption of palm dates sap which had been contaminated by infected fruit bats. (In Bangladesh in 2004)<br/><br />\r\n•    On the contrary, person-to-person transmission has also been documented which often includes the hospital setting in a nation.<br/><br />\r\n<p>Alongside this, the presence of NiV infection in people comprises a broader range of the clinical presentations which often ranges from the following: </p><br />\r\n•    Asymptomatic Infection <br/><br />\r\n•    Acute Respiratory Syndrome  <br/><br />\r\n•    Fatal Encephalitis  <br/><br />\r\n<p>This virus is so hazardous that it can also cause the diseases in pigs including other domestic animals and mammals too. Unfortunately, there is no vaccine for either humans or animals. However, the only primary treatment for human beings is just intensive support and care.</p><br />\r\n<p>As per the current scenario, the fatality rate of such case is actually estimated between 40% to 75% which may also vary with the disease\'s outbreak which definitely depends on the local capabilities for epidemiological surveillance and clinical management as well.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Virus Transferring Sources: </strong><br />\r\n<p>The virus can easily be transmitted to the human beings belonging to any age group via: <br/><br />\r\n•    Animals (such as bats or pigs)<br/><br />\r\n•    Contaminated foods <br/><br />\r\n•    It can also be transmitted directly from human-to-human <br/><br />\r\nWith the 2018\'s review, it is natural and we can also see that with such an alarming rate of the virus, there is an urgent need for accelerated research and development so that a frequent and permanent cure of the virus may easily be obtained. This is so because this virus has proven to be so dangerous and hazardous that it has become life-threatening too resulting in the death. Its a serious matter of the public\'s concerns which can\'t be ignored or overlooked. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Diagnosis:</strong><br />\r\n<p> Its diagnosis is not suspected at the time of presentation because its initial signs are also nonspecific. It can also hinder an accurate diagnosis while creates \'n\' number of the challenges in outbreak detection and outbreak response activities as well.<br/> <br />\r\nNipah virus infection can be only diagnosed with clinical history and convalescent phase of the disease where the fundamental main tests used are <br/><br />\r\n•    Real-time polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) from bodily fluids <br/><br />\r\n•    Antibody detection via enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) <br/><br />\r\n•    Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) assay <br/><br />\r\n•    Virus isolation by cell culture  <br/><br />\r\nHowever, intensive supportive care is always recommended in order to successfully and easily treat severe respiratory and neurologic complications. </p><br />\r\n <br />\r\n ',0,0,0,8000,1,'2020-02-13 15:40:09','2020-02-13 15:40:09'),(93,'5e4668cc05740',7,21,'Digital Age Interactivity: Increasing or Reducing the Physical Interaction in People','Digital Age Interactivity: Increasing or Reducing the Physical Interaction in People on social media','Digital_Tech.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbF','<strong>Digital Age Interactivity: Increasing or Reducing the Physical Interaction in People</strong> <br />\r\n<p>With the rising trend of social media these days, people prefer to meet and interact with their acquaintances via virtual mode. Seriously, in the present scenario, social networking sites have replaced the physical presence of the people into a completely new virtual world. Therein, it could be also determined that many various sorts of technologies can equally inhibit or enhance various forms of the interactivity and it’s all credit goes to IT (Information Technology). This is so because, in today’s virtual world, IT is the only major component that applies to social media simultaneously affecting as well as effecting the life of people. </p><br />\r\n<p>As we are talking about the interaction that has been transformed into the virtual domain, there exist different kinds of interactivity that people often take into consideration. Enlightening such concerns, find below some interactivity types: </p><br />\r\n<strong> Inherent interactivity </strong><br />\r\n<p>As its name itself suggest Inherent Interactivity, it fundamentally focusses on machine-based learning. Today, there have been most of the media platforms available on the Internet that are inherently active wherein, it pushes the people to react in a way like a behaviourist computer-based learning encourages people to react. It is not surprising that technologies that control a learner’s responses are often associated with more behaviourist approaches to learning.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Designed Interactivity </strong><br />\r\n<p>Several times it happens that some media gets utterly designed that automatically generates interest in the learners inclusive of engaging interactions. The concept could be understood with an instance. Suppose a webpage isn’t inherently active that it was expected to be but, on the other hand, it could be designed interactively to make the learners the informed and rational decisions or choices.</p> <br />\r\n<strong> User-Generated Interaction </strong><br />\r\n<p>This form of interactivity is oriented with the Digital Age. Some media doesn’t always comprise of the in-built interaction wherein, its end users could still interact either with some physical responses or cognitively. For instance, the concept could be better understood considering an incident of an art gallery. Several times, people inside the art gallery respond either emotionally or cognitively to some of the particular paintings while simultaneously others may just have a glance of it or simply passes by. As per the student’s concerns, they may choose to make sketches or drawings from the painting, etc.<br/> <br />\r\nNevertheless, media that is responsible both in encouraging and provoking people have also cost some associated advantages with it. Therein, it has somewhere improved and deteriorate the interaction’s quality that becomes difficult to analyse or monitor.</p> <br />\r\n<p> Henceforth, it could be analysed that somewhere digitization plays a prominent role and somewhere is a slippery component majorly when it comes in categorizing the media sources on the grounds of learning & interaction. This is so because both the instructors, as well as the learners, often have the options and preferences of choosing and using the medium pertaining that how it affects the learner’s interaction and feedback happening inside the single medium. Therefore, the design’s quality of having interactive experiences is highly important over the medium of interaction that enables activity.<br/> <br />\r\nHowever, it should also be noted that the technology’s choice can often reduce the activity’s level including the interaction’s quality. Alongside this, when it comes to the real scenarios, people are more likely to make use of an amalgamation of media assuring a quality-oriented and interactivity associated activities. Simultaneously, on the other hand, making use of varied media sources or channel are often likely to increase both the workload and the cost as well amid the learners and instructors. </p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,10000,1,'2020-02-14 15:00:52','2020-02-14 15:00:52'),(94,'5e4bd7366652c',3,502,'Do Parents give their children a Healthy Upbringing to leave them in Future?','Do Parents give their children a Healthy Upbringing to leave them in Future on social media','kids-care.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbG','<strong>Do Parents give their children a Healthy Upbringing to leave them in Future?</strong> <br />\r\n<p>Parents who invest their Morals & Values in their children always expect the best out of the results. They do so without any greed of themselves but for their children to be a good human being inclusive a follower of ‘humanity’. But, unfortunately, sometimes, the parents who nurture their children since childhood are found either in the Old Age Homes or in NGOs associated with elders. Also, these days, such scenarios are majorly happening because of financial disputes and property distribution. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Money Power over Relations</strong><br />\r\n<p>Relations have gone somewhere else and have left behind in the thirst and greed of money. Seriously for people these days, money power is everything above over the relationships and power of love as well. The child who gets upbringings from their parents is the first as well as the ones who kick them away. Such pain does the parents feel when their own children do an abrupt, as well as a brutal misbehave with them that at times, they start questioning themselves that are they really their children. </strong><br />\r\n<p>Since the birth of a child in the world, his parents always want to see the bucket full of blessings and smiles on his face. The main reason which brings the happiness and joy on the face of the parents of a child is that a child easily grasps the habits of picking up, imparting family dinners to their companions and educators, and becoming both socially and inwardly. But, neither a father nor a mother lets their child to leave them in the era of their crucial age i.e. in the old age, to distribute the property while betraying them and there are a lot of reasons that people these days have a lot of burden in their hearts via which they too curse their children. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Why parents are overwhelmed & burdened?</strong><br />\r\n<p>No parent curses their children and even no child wants to be cursed but unfortunately, today’s younger generation doesn’t understand and value their parents. Where spending family times have become old fashion & posting a picture with mom and dad on Mothers and Father’s Day have become a new societal trend of showing off the due respect.<br/> <br />\r\nOn the off chance, today’s children never want to be questioned and interrupted. In fact, they create a pool of questions in their psyche pertaining to their parents that why they always ask or tell them the things going around. This also indicates that conversing with the guardians takes away their liberty and privacy. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Children will always be Children </strong><br />\r\n<p>Children shall always remain the children for their parents. Also, no child could become a parent of his parent. This is an undenied truth and the cycle would go on. At certain times in life, everyone becomes a parent but not a parent of their parents. Thus, each child should need to understand the colossal measure of the pain that their parents feel and suffer from because of their wrongdoings. Additionally, this must be generally endeavoured to keep that put stock in place, regardless. <br/><br />\r\nEveryone should comprehend that guardians need their kid to flourish in an encompassing and sustaining environment that could have made them a good human being and not a beast to be hatred by other societal members. Hence, every parent wants their children to be a good human being who must not throw away his parents but shares family meals on a table as it delights them.<br/> <br />\r\nAlso, parents feel the tremendous amount of trust in their children that their children would always support them and withstands by them in the ups and downs in their life especially their old age. This is because a FAMILY which lives together grows together. Therefore, every parent wants their child to thrive in a surrounding that is nurturing, and clean to meet that structure, tirelessly.</p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,8000,1,'2020-02-18 17:53:18','2020-02-18 17:53:18'),(95,'5e53785395389',2,505,'Body Shaming: A Taboo or an Unacceptable Societal Realty','Body Shaming: A Taboo or an Unacceptable Societal Realty on social media','taboos.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbH','<strong>Body Shaming: A Taboo or an Unacceptable Societal Realty</strong><br />\r\n<p>For all of us living in this judgmental world, it becomes a natural tendency to always be and look better, stylish, faster and stronger. However, beholding this passion, we forget that this craze often results in severe mental disorders which later turn into mental health consequences majorly when it comes to an individual physical appearance.</p><br />\r\n<p>These days, portraying people who are either overweight or shorter in height has become very common by media and other associated sources. Such characters are highlighted like the running joke of the show that results in <strong>“lame fat jokes”</strong> as well as a crucial manifestation of self-doubt also termed as Body Shaming. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Body Shaming: A Drastic Bullying </strong><br />\r\n<p>A practice or an action of expressing humiliation about other people’s body gesture, size and shape are called body shaming. Majorly, it’s a form of bullying an individual that could be affected with a deeper emotional trauma wherein, teenage and young generation becomes a huge trap. Moreover, the worst part is that strangers or people passing by do comment on body shaming seems very common but uncommon fact is that, these days, body shaming is done by our near and dear ones such as friends, society’s acquaintances, relatives, friends, etc.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Comments & Taunts: WHY & HOW</strong><br />\r\n<p>Comments like, why does she wear that, why does he so fat, why are they short and fat or tall and skinny in fact, there is ‘n’ number of comments associated with the concept of body shaming. People commenting all such stuff even cannot imagine that to what extent do these comments and taunts can affect and hurt someone. Moreover, these humiliating concerns can downgrade the person that he/she starts doubting and questioning himself/herself like “I am so ugly”, “I am not handsome”, “Why I am so obese” and a lot more. </p><br />\r\n<p>Such kind of thoughts becomes so common and natural when a person becomes a victim of body shaming. Therefore, negative comments on someone’s body shape and size can extremely damage someone’s potential that leads a person towards low-self esteem, under-confident, anger, suicidal attempts, self-harm, and even body dysmorphic disorder.</p><br />\r\n<p>With such an alarming concern wherein, obesity has become a major social stigma has evolved a drastic as well as a serious issue for criticizing aspects of anyone’s body just because they are not being ideal. Unfortunately, with all such aspects, Indian societies have become extremely judgmental to judge everyone for a person’s appearance. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Manifestation’s Leading Results</strong><br />\r\n<p>The manifestation of body shaming can occur in different ways such as people shaming on you and oneself body shaming. This leaves a broader impact on people’s lives whilst feeling for their character. Such kind of a situation majorly results in criticism of one’s own appearance including other’s appearance in front of others via judgment or comparison with others. Alongside this, it also focuses on criticizing others without having knowledge of what to speak and what not. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Society need a change </strong><br />\r\n<p>Picking up of totally irrelevant flaws leads to shame and often perpetuates the ideology that people get judged only by their physical presence and features. These days, most of the magazines, advertisements as well as the social media platforms are continuously contributing to body shaming in varied different forms leading a normalize behavior amid the critics and sufferers. Most of the daily soaps, documentaries, and movies are following the pattern to change society’s ideology towards body shaming. <br/><br />\r\nThey have fallen to follow the pattern in such a way that an obese or a fat character is subjected to comic relief and criticism and helps people changing their mindsets. This is so because this kind of trending behavior majorly when it is focused on celebrity makes people help in understanding the arising potential consequences. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Can Body Shaming become a taboo?</strong><br />\r\n<p> Unlike any other kind of bullying, body shaming couldn’t become a taboo. It’s a victim only who has to stay positive and healthy in all the aspects accepting himself as it is. Also, society must also understand that commenting someone doesn’t make them feel appreciated instead generates a feeling of manifestation among the people that yes; seriously they have become a taboo for the society where they live. Natural appearance is not in one’s own hands if he or she is skinny or shorter, fatty or taller. Thus, it is mandatory for everyone to self-love.</p><br />\r\n<p> Also, the finest way to avoid such criticism is that, if anyone faces body shaming on social media then, he/she can instantly flag or report that particular content. National Eating Disorder Association (NEDA) has successfully stepped up in fighting and prohibiting against body shaming and encourages people who witness such concerns.</p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,10000,1,'2020-02-24 12:46:35','2020-02-24 12:46:35'),(96,'5e537d4076893',2,502,'Does Feminism is an Acceptable Reality or an Anti-Male Concept in the Society?','Does Feminism is an Acceptable Reality or an Anti-Male Concept in the Society on social media','Parana.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbI','<strong>Does Feminism is an Acceptable Reality or an Anti-Male Concept in the Society? <strong><br />\r\n<p>The term “Feminazi\" is a very broad term which is used pejoratively to describe either the feminists who are perceived as extreme or radical. Women who are entirely perceived as seeking superiority over men rather than equality or to describe all feminists. In the present scenario, the feminism advocates gender equality but it is largely misconstrued as an anti-male concept. <br/><br />\r\nFeminism has become a need of an hour as gender biasedness which is obviously an extremely sad reality today. Whereas, Feminism to us is equality. At the global times, there is not even a single man over woman and vice versa. The concept of feminism is a very misconstrued and misunderstood topic. This is because when we say feminism, it does not mean that all men should become subordinate and women should be the ones who rule the world. </p><br />\r\n<strong>A Real Feminism or Feminist Associated Meaning </strong><br />\r\n<p>The only way we or the today’s youth can have a progressive, as well as successful world, is when both men and women treat each other as equals without dominating each other and without any discrimination as well. However, everyone is aware that both men and women have different roles to play in every aspect of life so, they should complement each other rather than outdoing one another.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Where the Concept of Feminism is Applicable? </strong><br />\r\n<p>However, the concept of Feminism is deep to understand wherein, it doesn’t pertain to the women power over men dominance nor it means the women overwhelming attitudes in each aspect. On the broader scenario, the term feminism is applicable or is suitable on the grounds where women are not treated well where they are essentially required to be treated healthy. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Different Feminism’s Believes Pertaining to Different Meanings & Values </strong><br />\r\n<p>In accordance to orthodox traditions, some people believe that women are the crown of the men’s head, some believe that the women should be valued and treated under footsteps, behind every successful men there is a women and there are ‘n’ number of believes which have their own concepts and meanings. In fact, such mythologies are not completely true and even most of them are not acceptable by the society. Each believe has its own meaning and thinking behind its existence.</p><br />\r\n<strong> How to Treat & to be Treated? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Therein, it doesn’t indicate that women should be treated like a void or like everything above. This is so because, there is an old saying that a coin has two faces the heads and the tail, similarly, the concept of feminism has. If a woman will be treated like a void, she would always feel underestimated and if she would be treated like everything above then, sometimes it becomes dominance to males. However, it is again based and varies from a person to person that how one treats and how the other person gets treated. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Feminism’s CLOSING THOUGHTS… </strong><br />\r\n<p>Henceforth, the most important truth in the life of both the genders is that our reproductive organs are different and clearly there is a reason that why only a woman carry the baby. On the other hand, it is also noticeable and obviously, it does not mean that the man cannot help out with the caring of the child. Father is as much a nurturer as the mother. So, I can say that people who understand feminism can easily understand that men and women are equal but have different roles to play.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,9000,1,'2020-02-24 13:07:36','2020-02-24 13:07:36'),(97,'5e537e5c69d99',2,502,'Does Feminism is an Acceptable Reality or an Anti-Male Concept in the Society?','Does Feminism is an Acceptable Reality or an Anti-Male Concept in the Society on social media','Parana.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbJ','<strong>Does Feminism is an Acceptable Reality or an Anti-Male Concept in the Society? </strong><br />\r\n<p>The term “Feminazi\" is a very broad term which is used pejoratively to describe either the feminists who are perceived as extreme or radical. Women who are entirely perceived as seeking superiority over men rather than equality or to describe all feminists. In the present scenario, the feminism advocates gender equality but it is largely misconstrued as an anti-male concept. <br/><br />\r\nFeminism has become a need of an hour as gender biasedness which is obviously an extremely sad reality today. Whereas, Feminism to us is equality. At the global times, there is not even a single man over woman and vice versa. The concept of feminism is a very misconstrued and misunderstood topic. This is because when we say feminism, it does not mean that all men should become subordinate and women should be the ones who rule the world. </p><br />\r\n<strong>A Real Feminism or Feminist Associated Meaning </strong><br />\r\n<p>The only way we or the today’s youth can have a progressive, as well as successful world, is when both men and women treat each other as equals without dominating each other and without any discrimination as well. However, everyone is aware that both men and women have different roles to play in every aspect of life so, they should complement each other rather than outdoing one another.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Where the Concept of Feminism is Applicable? </strong><br />\r\n<p>However, the concept of Feminism is deep to understand wherein, it doesn’t pertain to the women power over men dominance nor it means the women overwhelming attitudes in each aspect. On the broader scenario, the term feminism is applicable or is suitable on the grounds where women are not treated well where they are essentially required to be treated healthy. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Different Feminism’s Believes Pertaining to Different Meanings & Values </strong><br />\r\n<p>In accordance to orthodox traditions, some people believe that women are the crown of the men’s head, some believe that the women should be valued and treated under footsteps, behind every successful men there is a women and there are ‘n’ number of believes which have their own concepts and meanings. In fact, such mythologies are not completely true and even most of them are not acceptable by the society. Each believe has its own meaning and thinking behind its existence.</p><br />\r\n<strong> How to Treat & to be Treated? </strong><br />\r\n<p>Therein, it doesn’t indicate that women should be treated like a void or like everything above. This is so because, there is an old saying that a coin has two faces the heads and the tail, similarly, the concept of feminism has. If a woman will be treated like a void, she would always feel underestimated and if she would be treated like everything above then, sometimes it becomes dominance to males. However, it is again based and varies from a person to person that how one treats and how the other person gets treated. </p><br />\r\n<strong>Feminism’s CLOSING THOUGHTS… </strong><br />\r\n<p>Henceforth, the most important truth in the life of both the genders is that our reproductive organs are different and clearly there is a reason that why only a woman carry the baby. On the other hand, it is also noticeable and obviously, it does not mean that the man cannot help out with the caring of the child. Father is as much a nurturer as the mother. So, I can say that people who understand feminism can easily understand that men and women are equal but have different roles to play.</p><br />\r\n ',0,0,0,10000,1,'2020-02-24 13:12:20','2020-02-24 13:12:20'),(98,'5e565efb35a6b',3,502,'Better Changing Lifestyle leads to Better Health & Wealth','Better Changing Lifestyle leads to Better Health & Wealth on social media','iStock.jpg','https://callupon.org/stbK','<strong>Better Changing Lifestyle leads to Better Health & Wealth </strong><br />\r\n<p>In the present scenario, with the busy schedule as well as working condition, the health of an individual gets completely ignored. In a hectic environment to earn money, people often compromise their health. Or in other words, in global times, the health of a person is secondary rather money is utmost. But why is it so? Doesn’t health is wealth is true? Yes, absolutely health is wealth is true if people take it seriously and follows the same. If your body is fit, then you can earn and attain everything of your wish and desire. Despite earning a sort of money which get consumed in maintaining health. </p><br />\r\n<p>It can be also understood that a healthy life is prone to a huge number of pitfalls. Owing to unhealthy living conditions and environments in the present industrialised world, the most important and highest affected factor is immunity. Today, a large number of people have become so sensitive to everything that they have developed the weaker immune system.</p><br />\r\n<strong>Availability of Diet in Synonymous Universe</strong><br />\r\n<p>Therefore, in order to maintain a lifestyle as well as the health of an individual, people are required to actively work in numerous domains such as weight management and lifestyle disorders. It proclaims a natural way of achieving a healthy lifestyle and do not endorse any kind of artificial methods such as machines, medicines, food supplements, dietary products etc. These days the word ‘diet’ has become synonymous with drastic weight loss, health loss, energy loss, metabolic rate loss and loss of sanity as well. So, over this, your perspective should believe that diet has to be a representation of what you eat in your life. Owing to such concerns, it is strongly recommended that the correct eating habit as a lifelong commitment and diet should be a reflection of this commitment.</p><br />\r\n<p>In addition to this, a better immune system could also be assisted with a couple of yoga and pranayama as well. It is scientifically proven that the eight angas of yoga are designed to build immunity in a human body and hence involve yogic exercises in our immunity booster programs.<br/><br />\r\nA Human can help Human to have a Good Health over Food Supplements<br/><br />\r\nAlso, instead of trying different food supplements that are effective for a shorter time span, it is also advisable to consult some good dieticians or lifestyle management specialist who strive in various or a large number of domains of oncological, food-allergy and gerontological nutrition. This is so because their experience and professionalism go through the case study of each and every individual and participate with them in close coordination.<br />\r\nSuch professionals are always found keen to learn about the health history of a patient, their favourite foods, their regular eating and exercise habits. They truly help everyone in setting the goals as well as the positive desires of their life and also help them in achieving the same. </p><br />\r\n<p>Apart from this, after processing the process of goal setting, prioritize your schedule. whilst focussing on your monitoring process to attain a better standard of living. Every individual should obey the perspective of his diet and daily routine to be a representation of what he eats in his entire life and could also inspire others. This is because, healthy as well as the good eating habits leads towards the good, healthier, happier and a prosper life. Owing to such of your own assistance you could not only be healthy alone but could also lead a healthy and wealthy nation ahead. As a result, such practice could often turn into a vital contribution to the welfare of the people and the upcoming generation for the sake of a healthy society.</p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n ',0,0,0,8000,1,'2020-02-26 17:35:15','2020-02-26 17:35:15');
